1
00:00:08,475 --> 00:00:12,274
[gentle instrumental music]

2
00:00:12,274 --> 00:00:14,988
‐ [Narrator] The history of
mankind is also

3
00:00:14,988 --> 00:00:17,076
a history of warfare.

4
00:00:17,076 --> 00:00:19,413
Why does humanity
foolishly repeat

5
00:00:19,413 --> 00:00:22,879
this endless series of
sad conflicts?

6
00:00:22,879 --> 00:00:26,302
Furthermore, why is it
that humans fight?

7
00:00:28,683 --> 00:00:31,522
‐ The Zabi family will shoulder
the responsibility

8
00:00:31,522 --> 00:00:33,108
of history to come.

9
00:00:34,151 --> 00:00:36,239
‐ [Narrator] Some people
fight for power

10
00:00:36,239 --> 00:00:38,953
on behalf of their family.

11
00:00:38,953 --> 00:00:41,499
[yelling]

12
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:43,713
[grunting]

13
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:49,516
‐ The Ral family, they're
hardly relevant anymore,

14
00:00:49,516 --> 00:00:52,772
not since you dragged their
bloody bodies through the mud.

15
00:00:52,772 --> 00:00:54,025
‐ [Narrator] While
there are others

16
00:00:54,025 --> 00:00:57,615
who are driven to fight by
their own pride.

17
00:00:59,160 --> 00:01:01,915
[metal creaking]

18
00:01:05,464 --> 00:01:07,927
And what about this young man?

19
00:01:07,927 --> 00:01:10,767
What is his reason for fighting?

20
00:01:10,767 --> 00:01:11,602
‐ Who cares?

21
00:01:11,602 --> 00:01:14,106
I am still Zeon Zum
Deikun's son.

22
00:01:14,106 --> 00:01:15,484
When I grow up,

23
00:01:15,484 --> 00:01:17,196
I will make the rest
of your family

24
00:01:17,196 --> 00:01:19,241
bow down before me.

25
00:01:19,241 --> 00:01:20,828
‐ Goodbye, Artesia.

26
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:24,753
‐ I told you I'm not Casval.

27
00:01:24,753 --> 00:01:26,674
My name's Char Aznable.

28
00:01:27,759 --> 00:01:32,351
[dramatic instrumental music]

29
00:01:32,351 --> 00:01:35,023
So this is twilight on the moon.

30
00:01:36,985 --> 00:01:40,367
[ship exploding]

31
00:01:40,367 --> 00:01:43,456
‐ [Announcer] Universal
Century 0068.

32
00:01:44,584 --> 00:01:47,924
It all began with the
death of this man,

33
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:50,262
[glass shattering]

34
00:01:50,262 --> 00:01:52,809
Zeon Zum Deikun, the
leader who called

35
00:01:52,809 --> 00:01:55,523
for Spacenoid independence.

36
00:01:55,523 --> 00:01:57,317
‐ Your father was assassinated,

37
00:01:57,317 --> 00:02:00,240
murdered by those Zabi thieves.

38
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:02,077
‐ Listen, the political
tension has put us

39
00:02:02,077 --> 00:02:03,914
on the verge of a blood bath.

40
00:02:03,914 --> 00:02:06,085
[yelling]

41
00:02:07,839 --> 00:02:10,720
‐ [Narrator] Universal
Century 0069.

42
00:02:10,720 --> 00:02:13,224
‐ The Federation is
Deikun's enemy.

43
00:02:13,224 --> 00:02:14,811
‐ We want freedom.

44
00:02:14,811 --> 00:02:16,272
‐ [Narrator] In these
turbulent times,

45
00:02:16,272 --> 00:02:19,613
the unrest from within the space
colonies of Side Three,

46
00:02:19,613 --> 00:02:21,658
just beyond the moon,
boils over,

47
00:02:21,658 --> 00:02:26,167
as cries for independence from
the Earth Federation grow.

48
00:02:26,167 --> 00:02:28,087
Universal Century 0071.

49
00:02:29,048 --> 00:02:31,010
[guns firing]

50
00:02:31,010 --> 00:02:32,429
To further advance things,

51
00:02:32,429 --> 00:02:34,391
Zeon is in the process
of developing

52
00:02:34,391 --> 00:02:36,688
a new weapon in
preparation for war

53
00:02:36,688 --> 00:02:38,609
against the Federation.

54
00:02:40,571 --> 00:02:43,911
‐ [Dozle] And it is going to
crush the Federation.

55
00:02:43,911 --> 00:02:47,042
‐ [Narrator] Universal
Century 0077.

56
00:02:47,042 --> 00:02:47,919
‐ Your choice.

57
00:02:47,919 --> 00:02:49,129
You can hang back,

58
00:02:49,129 --> 00:02:50,716
or you can crank the
gears of history

59
00:02:50,716 --> 00:02:52,344
with your own two hands.

60
00:02:52,344 --> 00:02:54,933
‐ Alright, then let's move out.

61
00:02:57,354 --> 00:02:59,233
‐ [Narrator] The animosity
towards the Federation

62
00:02:59,233 --> 00:03:01,822
from within Zeon reaches
its breaking point,

63
00:03:01,822 --> 00:03:02,907
and a counter offensive

64
00:03:02,907 --> 00:03:04,995
against Federation
security forces

65
00:03:04,995 --> 00:03:08,042
is launched by its military
academy cadets.

66
00:03:08,042 --> 00:03:08,878
‐ Now.

67
00:03:09,963 --> 00:03:12,719
[weapons firing]

68
00:03:14,723 --> 00:03:16,142
‐ We're just a colony state.

69
00:03:16,142 --> 00:03:18,438
There's no way we'll win
against the Federation.

70
00:03:18,438 --> 00:03:19,524
‐ Yes, maybe.

71
00:03:20,902 --> 00:03:23,489
But we won't know until we try.

72
00:03:24,993 --> 00:03:28,499
‐ [Narrator] And now a
showdown is imminent.

73
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:30,045
‐ Those poor children,

74
00:03:30,045 --> 00:03:34,345
why were they fated to be
Deikun's progeny?

75
00:03:34,345 --> 00:03:36,683
[gentle instrumental music]

76
00:03:36,683 --> 00:03:38,771
Grow to be nice girl.

77
00:03:38,771 --> 00:03:42,152
Then grow up to be a
good person.

78
00:03:42,152 --> 00:03:45,492
Then you can make a lot
of people happy.

79
00:03:46,536 --> 00:03:47,580
‐ [Narrator] But the siblings'
lives

80
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:50,670
remain at the mercy of
these cruel times

81
00:03:50,670 --> 00:03:53,174
and their unfortunate fate.

82
00:03:53,174 --> 00:03:55,345
[yelling]

83
00:04:01,148 --> 00:04:03,444
‐ I would wish to be
with my children

84
00:04:03,444 --> 00:04:05,574
for just one more night.

85
00:04:05,574 --> 00:04:07,035
‐ It's just so unfair.

86
00:04:07,035 --> 00:04:08,872
It's so sad.

87
00:04:08,872 --> 00:04:10,876
She's going to die soon.

88
00:04:13,381 --> 00:04:15,761
‐ [Narrator] Perhaps these two
were never destined

89
00:04:15,761 --> 00:04:18,474
to have a moment's peace.

90
00:04:18,474 --> 00:04:22,065
[gentle instrumental music]

91
00:04:22,065 --> 00:04:24,319
‐ Artesia, it's mother.

92
00:04:24,319 --> 00:04:25,238
She's dead.

93
00:04:26,825 --> 00:04:29,706
[gasping]

94
00:04:29,706 --> 00:04:32,002
‐ [Narrator] With the loss
of his mother‐‐

95
00:04:32,002 --> 00:04:34,841
‐ Please, you can't leave me,
brother.

96
00:04:34,841 --> 00:04:35,676
Casval.

97
00:04:37,304 --> 00:04:38,139
Don't go.

98
00:04:39,768 --> 00:04:40,978
‐ [Narrator] And now separated

99
00:04:40,978 --> 00:04:42,940
from his only remaining family,

100
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:44,527
his younger sister,

101
00:04:45,696 --> 00:04:48,201
the man sets out to get revenge.

102
00:04:48,201 --> 00:04:50,706
[guns firing]

103
00:04:52,502 --> 00:04:55,256
[ship exploding]

104
00:04:58,806 --> 00:04:59,974
In his mind,

105
00:04:59,974 --> 00:05:03,816
revenge itself is a noble
and righteous cause,

106
00:05:05,653 --> 00:05:08,491
and so humanity rushes
on towards a war

107
00:05:08,491 --> 00:05:11,665
the likes of which it
has never known.

108
00:05:12,625 --> 00:05:14,461
‐ Our chance to forge a
new relationship

109
00:05:14,461 --> 00:05:16,382
with the Federation,

110
00:05:16,382 --> 00:05:19,429
however, we do have a
few conditions,

111
00:05:20,473 --> 00:05:22,603
that the Federation relinquish
their assets here

112
00:05:22,603 --> 00:05:24,774
and withdraw their forces.

113
00:05:26,235 --> 00:05:28,281
‐ It looks like the world
is determined.

114
00:05:28,281 --> 00:05:30,661
It's going to see
this to the end.

115
00:05:30,661 --> 00:05:34,459
[dramatic instrumental music]

116
00:05:38,342 --> 00:05:39,178
‐ Fire.

117
00:05:40,221 --> 00:05:43,102
[weapons firing]

118
00:05:43,102 --> 00:05:44,856
‐ [Narrator] Mobile suits, the
weapons that Zeon

119
00:05:44,856 --> 00:05:46,275
had secretly developed,

120
00:05:46,275 --> 00:05:48,154
debut in battle.

121
00:05:48,154 --> 00:05:49,782
[gasping]

122
00:05:49,782 --> 00:05:51,661
[weapons firing]

123
00:05:51,661 --> 00:05:55,836
And they possess fearsome
combat capabilities.

124
00:05:55,836 --> 00:05:58,592
[metal clanging]

125
00:06:00,846 --> 00:06:02,850
‐ Dr. Minovsky succeeded.

126
00:06:02,850 --> 00:06:05,271
He's finally actually
made it happen.

127
00:06:05,271 --> 00:06:06,775
‐ Show those Federation scumbags

128
00:06:06,775 --> 00:06:08,528
what real Mobile Suits can do.

129
00:06:08,528 --> 00:06:12,369
[dramatic instrumental music]

130
00:06:15,626 --> 00:06:18,256
‐ Another sucker bites the dust.

131
00:06:20,051 --> 00:06:21,972
‐ I'll let that sink in a bit,

132
00:06:21,972 --> 00:06:23,432
for this is the kind of power

133
00:06:23,432 --> 00:06:25,854
that Zeon already possesses.

134
00:06:25,854 --> 00:06:28,401
My father will name himself
as its sovereign,

135
00:06:28,401 --> 00:06:31,365
and he'll declare our
independence any day now.

136
00:06:31,365 --> 00:06:32,367
‐ Sieg Zeon.

137
00:06:33,327 --> 00:06:35,290
‐ [Crowd] Sieg Zeon,

138
00:06:35,290 --> 00:06:36,125
Sieg Zeon,

139
00:06:37,460 --> 00:06:38,296
Sieg Zeon.

140
00:06:39,464 --> 00:06:43,306
[dramatic instrumental music]

141
00:06:44,934 --> 00:06:46,478
‐ My enemy, your enemy,

142
00:06:46,478 --> 00:06:48,692
everyone's enemy,

143
00:06:48,692 --> 00:06:50,904
and I'm gonna take them out.

144
00:06:50,904 --> 00:06:54,327
[dramatic instrumental music]

145
00:06:54,327 --> 00:06:55,246
‐ Fire.

146
00:06:55,246 --> 00:06:58,628
[weapons firing]

147
00:06:58,628 --> 00:06:59,463
‐ Stop it.

148
00:06:59,463 --> 00:07:01,300
Don't do this, Casval.

149
00:07:02,469 --> 00:07:04,974
[tank firing]

150
00:07:06,477 --> 00:07:08,105
‐ [Sayla] And you, dear Casval,

151
00:07:08,105 --> 00:07:09,232
could it be true?

152
00:07:09,232 --> 00:07:11,529
Are you really gone forever?

153
00:07:11,529 --> 00:07:12,990
‐ [Narrator] Whenever the
righteous causes

154
00:07:12,990 --> 00:07:15,621
of different groups of
people clash,

155
00:07:15,621 --> 00:07:17,123
the result is war.

156
00:07:20,254 --> 00:07:22,425
[gasping]

157
00:07:25,348 --> 00:07:27,185
‐ I present the RX‐78,

158
00:07:28,855 --> 00:07:30,191
codename Gundam.

159
00:07:31,778 --> 00:07:33,824
[dramatic instrumental music]

160
00:07:33,824 --> 00:07:35,994
[gasping]

161
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:39,251
‐ [Narrator] After all
that's been sacrificed,

162
00:07:39,251 --> 00:07:42,423
will we ever see the end of
this man's war?

163
00:07:42,423 --> 00:07:44,344
‐ Everything's red.

164
00:07:44,344 --> 00:07:47,058
I think I rather like it.

165
00:07:47,058 --> 00:07:48,687
[guns firing]

166
00:07:48,687 --> 00:07:52,528
[dramatic instrumental music]

167
00:07:56,995 --> 00:07:58,497
‐ Stop it, Casval.

168
00:07:59,332 --> 00:08:03,174
[dramatic instrumental music]

169
00:08:05,762 --> 00:08:08,475
[gun cocking]

170
00:08:08,475 --> 00:08:11,106
‐ [Narrator] The worst war
in human history

171
00:08:11,106 --> 00:08:12,610
is about to begin.

172
00:08:14,404 --> 00:08:18,245
[dramatic instrumental music]

173
00:09:00,246 --> 00:09:02,960
[weapons firing]

174
00:09:07,636 --> 00:09:09,557
Universal Century 0079,

175
00:09:10,851 --> 00:09:11,853
January 3rd,

176
00:09:13,523 --> 00:09:16,069
the Principality of
Zeon declares war

177
00:09:16,069 --> 00:09:17,615
on the Earth Federation.

178
00:09:17,615 --> 00:09:20,244
[weapons firing]

179
00:09:20,244 --> 00:09:24,294
The Zeon fleet, led by Vice
Admiral Dozle Zabi,

180
00:09:24,294 --> 00:09:26,799
crushes the EFSF's
cruiser fleet,

181
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:28,637
utterly wiping it out.

182
00:09:30,515 --> 00:09:32,310
A Mobile Suit assault force,

183
00:09:32,310 --> 00:09:35,024
led by Major General
Kycilia Zabi,

184
00:09:35,024 --> 00:09:38,531
seizes control of the lunar
city of Granada.

185
00:09:38,531 --> 00:09:41,621
She then goes on to capture
Von Braun as well.

186
00:09:41,621 --> 00:09:45,545
[dramatic instrumental music]

187
00:09:45,545 --> 00:09:48,300
[weapons firing]

188
00:10:11,430 --> 00:10:13,225
‐ I can still fight.

189
00:10:13,225 --> 00:10:17,066
[dramatic instrumental music]

190
00:10:23,705 --> 00:10:25,499
‐ [Narrator] On that
exact same day,

191
00:10:25,499 --> 00:10:27,713
Zeon also declares war against

192
00:10:27,713 --> 00:10:30,886
and attacks Side Two,
called Hatte,

193
00:10:30,886 --> 00:10:32,472
which had steadfastly maintained

194
00:10:32,472 --> 00:10:34,267
an anti‐Zeon stance.

195
00:10:34,267 --> 00:10:35,896
‐ Fire and brimstone
has rained down

196
00:10:35,896 --> 00:10:38,442
from the heavens onto Side Two,

197
00:10:38,442 --> 00:10:39,820
just desserts for anyone

198
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,616
who would dare harbor opposition

199
00:10:41,616 --> 00:10:44,412
to the noble Spacenoid cause.

200
00:10:44,412 --> 00:10:45,582
They've received punishment

201
00:10:45,582 --> 00:10:48,630
they brought down upon
their own heads.

202
00:10:48,630 --> 00:10:51,384
[weapons firing]

203
00:11:00,654 --> 00:11:02,825
[yelling]

204
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,962
[weapons firing]

205
00:11:08,962 --> 00:11:11,676
[ship exploding]

206
00:11:20,569 --> 00:11:21,779
‐ [Man] Commander,

207
00:11:21,779 --> 00:11:23,031
Commander Ral, we've
eliminated most

208
00:11:23,031 --> 00:11:25,202
of the enemy's resistance.

209
00:11:26,664 --> 00:11:28,751
‐ You can't call this a war.

210
00:11:28,751 --> 00:11:31,089
‐ I've recognized that it
was the Federation

211
00:11:31,089 --> 00:11:32,300
that poisoned the minds

212
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:34,638
of the foolish leaders of Hatte.

213
00:11:34,638 --> 00:11:36,559
They are the true enemy.

214
00:11:36,559 --> 00:11:39,314
[weapons firing]

215
00:11:40,859 --> 00:11:42,696
‐ It's a slaughter.

216
00:11:42,696 --> 00:11:46,704
My countrymen, you 150 million
citizens of Zeon,

217
00:11:48,081 --> 00:11:50,294
our fight has only just begun.

218
00:11:50,294 --> 00:11:52,381
Let us continue to march onwards

219
00:11:52,381 --> 00:11:54,970
together in perfect unison,

220
00:11:54,970 --> 00:11:58,645
and we will not cease until
we have victory.

221
00:11:59,563 --> 00:12:01,316
[weapons firing]

222
00:12:01,316 --> 00:12:05,157
[dramatic instrumental music]

223
00:12:23,026 --> 00:12:26,701
[gentle instrumental music]

224
00:12:47,576 --> 00:12:49,788
‐ The fighting in
Hatte continues.

225
00:12:49,788 --> 00:12:51,499
Yesterday evening, the
Hatte government

226
00:12:51,499 --> 00:12:53,170
put out a call to all colonies

227
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:56,009
in the Federation government
for military support.

228
00:12:56,009 --> 00:12:58,514
The Zeon force's attack range
appears to encompass

229
00:12:58,514 --> 00:13:00,518
almost all of Hatte's Banshee‐‐

230
00:13:00,518 --> 00:13:02,564
‐ Uh, it's me, Hayato.

231
00:13:02,564 --> 00:13:04,610
Kai wants you to come out, okay?

232
00:13:04,610 --> 00:13:05,904
‐ [Reporter] The capital Banshee

233
00:13:05,904 --> 00:13:07,281
given the difference in
fighting strength

234
00:13:07,281 --> 00:13:09,494
between them and the
Zeon attack force,

235
00:13:09,494 --> 00:13:11,874
they are at a clear
disadvantage.

236
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,503
With the exception of Side Six‐‐

237
00:13:13,503 --> 00:13:14,295
‐ [Robot] Don't go.

238
00:13:14,295 --> 00:13:15,924
Kai is a bad egg.

239
00:13:15,924 --> 00:13:17,343
Do not go, Amuro.

240
00:13:18,805 --> 00:13:21,519
‐ This is no time to stay
cooped up all alone.

241
00:13:21,519 --> 00:13:25,484
Haven't you heard there's
a war going on?

242
00:13:25,484 --> 00:13:27,113
‐ I wasn't really aware.

243
00:13:27,113 --> 00:13:28,825
‐ Your old man, isn't
he in charge

244
00:13:28,825 --> 00:13:30,870
of the development
sector or something?

245
00:13:30,870 --> 00:13:32,039
‐ I know.

246
00:13:32,039 --> 00:13:34,628
What if he's actually secretly a
member of the military?

247
00:13:34,628 --> 00:13:36,799
[gasping]

248
00:13:38,176 --> 00:13:42,017
[dramatic instrumental music]

249
00:13:46,067 --> 00:13:49,533
‐ Guys, if we're gonna check out
the development sector,

250
00:13:49,533 --> 00:13:50,785
let's go already,

251
00:13:50,785 --> 00:13:54,125
or I'll be late for Judo
practice this morning.

252
00:13:54,125 --> 00:13:55,419
‐ Are you actually
gonna go there?

253
00:13:55,419 --> 00:13:57,507
‐ Something's fishy
about the place,

254
00:13:57,507 --> 00:14:00,930
so I'm gonna figure out what it
is they're hiding.

255
00:14:00,930 --> 00:14:02,141
‐ No, you can't.

256
00:14:02,141 --> 00:14:04,103
My dad told me not to go
anywhere near that place.

257
00:14:04,103 --> 00:14:06,692
‐ You're too much of a
daddy's boy, Amuro.

258
00:14:06,692 --> 00:14:09,113
If all you do is follow your
parents' orders all the time,

259
00:14:09,113 --> 00:14:11,451
then how do you expect to grow,
huh?

260
00:14:11,451 --> 00:14:13,038
Be your own man.

261
00:14:13,038 --> 00:14:15,375
Come on, you know I'm right.

262
00:14:16,545 --> 00:14:18,716
[murmuring]

263
00:14:18,716 --> 00:14:20,135
[truck engine running]

264
00:14:20,135 --> 00:14:23,224
Okay, development sector,
here we go.

265
00:14:26,314 --> 00:14:27,984
[murmuring]

266
00:14:27,984 --> 00:14:29,320
♫ Here comes Seven

267
00:14:29,320 --> 00:14:30,990
♫ Side Seven

268
