♫ Straight to victory roads

269
00:14:32,284 --> 00:14:34,121
♫ Go ai, ai, oh

270
00:14:34,121 --> 00:14:35,332
[dramatic instrumental music]

271
00:14:35,332 --> 00:14:36,543
♫ Here comes Seven

272
00:14:36,543 --> 00:14:38,171
♫ Side Seven

273
00:14:38,171 --> 00:14:39,675
♫ Straight to victory roads

274
00:14:39,675 --> 00:14:42,346
♫ Go ai, ai, oh

275
00:14:46,354 --> 00:14:48,526
[gasping]

276
00:14:51,573 --> 00:14:54,453
‐ Hey, Kai, don't you think this
looks kind of dangerous?

277
00:14:54,453 --> 00:14:55,288
‐ Huh?

278
00:14:55,288 --> 00:14:56,249
What's that?

279
00:14:56,249 --> 00:14:58,003
Move it, you chicken.

280
00:14:59,506 --> 00:15:00,340
[truck engine running]

281
00:15:00,340 --> 00:15:01,342
‐ What the‐‐

282
00:15:02,595 --> 00:15:04,181
‐ When you want a
job done right,

283
00:15:04,181 --> 00:15:05,518
call Kai Shiden.

284
00:15:06,352 --> 00:15:07,731
[truck engine running]

285
00:15:07,731 --> 00:15:09,901
[yelling]

286
00:15:24,765 --> 00:15:26,100
Go.

287
00:15:26,100 --> 00:15:28,522
[truck engine running]

288
00:15:28,522 --> 00:15:31,194
[yelling]

289
00:15:31,194 --> 00:15:32,572
‐ Please stop, Kai.

290
00:15:32,572 --> 00:15:33,741
‐ What's the big deal?

291
00:15:33,741 --> 00:15:35,368
They're supposed to be
developing this area

292
00:15:35,368 --> 00:15:38,124
into new living quarters for
all of us, right?

293
00:15:38,124 --> 00:15:39,669
So we're just gonna
have ourselves

294
00:15:39,669 --> 00:15:42,509
a little sneak peak at what's
on the other side

295
00:15:42,509 --> 00:15:44,220
of that wall.

296
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:47,644
[grunting and murmuring]

297
00:15:51,234 --> 00:15:53,906
[siren ringing]

298
00:15:59,584 --> 00:16:02,297
[weapons firing]

299
00:16:07,099 --> 00:16:09,228
[yelling]

300
00:16:16,827 --> 00:16:18,121
‐ [Man] Do not resist.

301
00:16:18,121 --> 00:16:20,585
Step out of the
vehicle immediately.

302
00:16:20,585 --> 00:16:22,462
I repeat, step out
of the vehicle

303
00:16:22,462 --> 00:16:24,843
with your hands in the air.

304
00:16:24,843 --> 00:16:27,472
If you resist, we will
open fire again.

305
00:16:27,472 --> 00:16:30,228
[boots thumping]

306
00:16:35,615 --> 00:16:38,704
‐ Those guys are
Federation soldiers.

307
00:16:39,581 --> 00:16:40,958
[grunting]

308
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:44,298
‐ Goddammit, what the hell were
you delinquents thinking?

309
00:16:44,298 --> 00:16:46,970
Alright, which of you
dumbasses is the leader?

310
00:16:46,970 --> 00:16:49,475
I'm guessing it's you.

311
00:16:49,475 --> 00:16:51,730
[grunting]

312
00:16:54,569 --> 00:16:57,115
Now, I wanna see all your IDs.

313
00:16:57,115 --> 00:16:58,911
I'm confiscating them.

314
00:16:58,911 --> 00:17:00,330
‐ Hand them over.

315
00:17:05,048 --> 00:17:05,883
Commander.

316
00:17:06,885 --> 00:17:09,223
[murmuring]

317
00:17:10,392 --> 00:17:12,479
‐ Hey, loser, I mean you.

318
00:17:16,153 --> 00:17:17,155
Is it true?

319
00:17:17,155 --> 00:17:19,619
Are you really Chief
Tem Ray's son?

320
00:17:19,619 --> 00:17:22,291
‐ Uh, yes, that's correct, sir.

321
00:17:22,291 --> 00:17:23,711
‐ Well, why didn't
you tell us that

322
00:17:23,711 --> 00:17:25,715
right off the bat, old buddy?

323
00:17:25,715 --> 00:17:27,342
[laughing]

324
00:17:27,342 --> 00:17:29,639
No need for you to stay here
with the riff raff.

325
00:17:29,639 --> 00:17:33,772
How about I have someone
escort you home?

326
00:17:33,772 --> 00:17:35,818
You're not off the hook,
you punks.

327
00:17:35,818 --> 00:17:38,574
Why in the world would you pull
a stupid stunt like that?

328
00:17:38,574 --> 00:17:40,493
You looking for a
beating or something?

329
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:42,205
Well, you're gonna get one.

330
00:17:42,205 --> 00:17:44,460
[grunting]

331
00:17:49,512 --> 00:17:50,472
[birds chirping]

332
00:17:50,472 --> 00:17:51,975
‐ I'm sorry to announce
there has been

333
00:17:51,975 --> 00:17:54,104
a most unfortunate incident.

334
00:17:54,104 --> 00:17:57,152
Several students in this class
stole a construction vehicle

335
00:17:57,152 --> 00:18:00,158
and attempted to enter the
development sector.

336
00:18:00,158 --> 00:18:02,204
Thank goodness they
were released,

337
00:18:02,204 --> 00:18:03,582
but anyone else who gets caught

338
00:18:03,582 --> 00:18:06,379
may not get off as
easily next time.

339
00:18:06,379 --> 00:18:08,174
As you know, war has broken out

340
00:18:08,174 --> 00:18:11,640
between the Principality of Zeon
and the Earth Federation.

341
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:12,809
During this crisis,

342
00:18:12,809 --> 00:18:16,357
we must do our utmost to avoid
dangerous activities.

343
00:18:16,357 --> 00:18:18,779
That includes to not under
any circumstances

344
00:18:18,779 --> 00:18:20,908
go near the development sector.

345
00:18:20,908 --> 00:18:22,578
Is that clear?

346
00:18:22,578 --> 00:18:26,252
[gentle instrumental music]

347
00:18:37,441 --> 00:18:39,821
‐ [Man] Commander Ramba Ral,
entering the bridge.

348
00:18:39,821 --> 00:18:41,908
‐ Ah, great, you're here.

349
00:18:44,622 --> 00:18:47,419
The initial fleet battle was a
complete victory.

350
00:18:47,419 --> 00:18:49,298
We sure showed that high
and mighty Reval

351
00:18:49,298 --> 00:18:50,551
a thing or two.

352
00:18:52,262 --> 00:18:56,020
Hey, now, what's with
the long face?

353
00:18:56,020 --> 00:18:58,316
Isn't our victory worth
a little smile?

354
00:18:58,316 --> 00:19:01,113
‐ Truth be told, I would have
much rather participated

355
00:19:01,113 --> 00:19:02,909
in a fleet battle.

356
00:19:02,909 --> 00:19:05,831
Hatte's defense forces are of
little to no consequence.

357
00:19:05,831 --> 00:19:08,169
I saw no need to
declare war on them.

358
00:19:08,169 --> 00:19:10,508
‐ Come on, don't be like that.

359
00:19:10,508 --> 00:19:13,221
‐ That's Island Iffish,
isn't it?

360
00:19:13,221 --> 00:19:14,724
We could have taken it
in half a day

361
00:19:14,724 --> 00:19:16,018
if we chose to,

362
00:19:16,018 --> 00:19:19,024
and yet we were ordered to
leave it untouched.

363
00:19:19,024 --> 00:19:22,197
‐ Precisely, that's why I
called you here.

364
00:19:22,197 --> 00:19:24,243
Our brilliant Supreme
Leader Gihren

365
00:19:24,243 --> 00:19:26,288
came up with an ingenious plan.

366
00:19:26,288 --> 00:19:29,002
In one stroke, he will put an
immediate end to this war,

367
00:19:29,002 --> 00:19:32,467
ensuring Zeon a
decisive victory.

368
00:19:32,467 --> 00:19:33,971
‐ We are going to murder
those citizens

369
00:19:33,971 --> 00:19:35,306
and drop a colony?

370
00:19:35,306 --> 00:19:38,897
‐ Sh, you may want to
rephrase that.

371
00:19:38,897 --> 00:19:39,816
The way you're putting it,

372
00:19:39,816 --> 00:19:43,447
it makes it sounds like we're
doing something wrong.

373
00:19:43,447 --> 00:19:44,576
You there.

374
00:19:44,576 --> 00:19:45,619
‐ [Soldiers] Yes, sir.

375
00:19:45,619 --> 00:19:48,542
‐ This is confidential between
me and the commander.

376
00:19:48,542 --> 00:19:49,669
Now get lost.

377
00:19:49,669 --> 00:19:50,588
‐ Yes, sir.

378
00:19:55,054 --> 00:19:57,560
‐ Listen, this is war time here.

379
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:58,812
If we're at war with Hatte,

380
00:19:58,812 --> 00:20:00,148
then they're the enemy.

381
00:20:00,148 --> 00:20:01,400
Don't you get that.

382
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,235
‐ I know.

383
00:20:02,235 --> 00:20:03,697
‐ I'm not done.

384
00:20:03,697 --> 00:20:06,076
Before you say anything,

385
00:20:06,076 --> 00:20:08,164
take a look at this here.

386
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:11,755
We'll attach external
engines to the colony,

387
00:20:11,755 --> 00:20:12,965
take it out of orbit,

388
00:20:12,965 --> 00:20:14,928
send it into low Earth orbit,

389
00:20:14,928 --> 00:20:18,852
and drop it on Federation
General HQ at Jaburo.

390
00:20:19,979 --> 00:20:21,566
You get it now?

391
00:20:21,566 --> 00:20:23,862
They anticipated they'd be
going to war with us

392
00:20:23,862 --> 00:20:25,323
and even prepped for it.

393
00:20:25,323 --> 00:20:28,287
How else do explain building the
new Jaburo Headquarters

394
00:20:28,287 --> 00:20:30,375
under 1,000 meters of bedrock?

395
00:20:30,375 --> 00:20:32,045
But this will smash it.

396
00:20:32,045 --> 00:20:33,381
‐ And I'm to carry this out?

397
00:20:33,381 --> 00:20:35,134
‐ Exactly, with the assistance

398
00:20:35,134 --> 00:20:36,888
of your Mobile Suit team.

399
00:20:36,888 --> 00:20:39,059
‐ I will do no such thing.

400
00:20:39,936 --> 00:20:41,397
‐ What did you say?

401
00:20:41,397 --> 00:20:42,650
‐ I get it now.

402
00:20:42,650 --> 00:20:44,946
Lord Gihren would plan
something like this.

403
00:20:44,946 --> 00:20:48,704
However, a military man should
never even suggest this

404
00:20:48,704 --> 00:20:50,373
because it's the work
of the devil.

405
00:20:50,373 --> 00:20:51,500
It's evil.

406
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:54,131
‐ You dare call me a devil.

407
00:20:54,131 --> 00:20:55,174
Look who's talking.

408
00:20:55,174 --> 00:20:57,178
That makes you a hypocrite.

409
00:20:57,178 --> 00:20:58,807
You have the blood of
hundreds of millions

410
00:20:58,807 --> 00:21:00,728
of Hatte civilians
on your hands.

411
00:21:00,728 --> 00:21:02,272
If anyone here is the devil,

412
00:21:02,272 --> 00:21:03,775
that would be you.

413
00:21:03,775 --> 00:21:07,282
Those poor souls are going to
wind up dead anyway.

414
00:21:07,282 --> 00:21:08,117
At least this way,

415
00:21:08,117 --> 00:21:09,829
their deaths are counting
for something.

416
00:21:09,829 --> 00:21:10,664
When you think about it,

417
00:21:10,664 --> 00:21:12,250
it's the most sensible option.

418
00:21:12,250 --> 00:21:13,920
‐ No it is not.

419
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:15,048
‐ Why not?

420
00:21:15,048 --> 00:21:17,010
Why don't you agree?

421
00:21:17,010 --> 00:21:19,891
[yelling]

422
00:21:19,891 --> 00:21:23,523
‐ Admiral Dozle, this war
is sheer insanity.

423
00:21:23,523 --> 00:21:25,736
Zeon Zum Deikun would
never approve

424
00:21:25,736 --> 00:21:27,280
of such a thing,

425
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:30,161
and so I refuse to
take part in it.

426
00:21:30,161 --> 00:21:31,497
‐ Wait.

427
00:21:31,497 --> 00:21:32,499
I said wait.

428
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:35,004
Did you forget I was responsible

429
00:21:35,004 --> 00:21:38,344
for your double rank promotion,
you ingrate?

430
00:21:38,344 --> 00:21:39,346
‐ Step aside.

431
00:21:39,346 --> 00:21:40,974
You're in the way.

432
00:21:40,974 --> 00:21:42,060
‐ Stop.

433
00:21:42,060 --> 00:21:43,312
Come back here.

434
00:21:45,984 --> 00:21:47,613
Wait, damn you.

435
00:21:47,613 --> 00:21:49,659
You're going to regret
this decision,

436
00:21:49,659 --> 00:21:50,828
mark my words.

437
00:21:53,124 --> 00:21:57,173
[dramatic instrumental music]

438
00:21:57,173 --> 00:21:59,344
[yelling]

439
00:22:01,891 --> 00:22:02,726
[guns firing]

440
00:22:02,726 --> 00:22:04,981
‐ Hey, don't waste ammo.

441
00:22:04,981 --> 00:22:05,816
‐ That's right.

442
00:22:05,816 --> 00:22:06,860
You tell them.

443
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:09,615
Just wait, we're
gonna show them.

444
00:22:10,951 --> 00:22:12,203
‐ Yuki.

445
00:22:12,203 --> 00:22:15,878
‐ Fan Lee, where are
you guys going?

446
00:22:15,878 --> 00:22:17,923
‐ We're evacuating to
the shelter.

447
00:22:17,923 --> 00:22:19,217
What about you?

448
00:22:19,217 --> 00:22:21,346
‐ The docking bay
for guard duty.

449
00:22:21,346 --> 00:22:25,939
‐ Wait, what are you, [yelling].

450
00:22:25,939 --> 00:22:27,693
You could have broken your neck.

451
00:22:27,693 --> 00:22:30,323
You should come along with
us to the shelter.

452
00:22:30,323 --> 00:22:32,410
‐ No way, I'm not running away.

453
00:22:32,410 --> 00:22:34,289
I'll escort you though.

454
00:22:35,374 --> 00:22:38,088
[boots clomping]

455
00:22:42,347 --> 00:22:44,226
‐ Hey, the other Banshees,

456
00:22:44,226 --> 00:22:46,773
do you think that they
also lost to Zeon?

457
00:22:46,773 --> 00:22:48,025
‐ Probably.

458
00:22:48,025 --> 00:22:50,404
[murmuring]

459
00:22:50,404 --> 00:22:51,908
Cheer up.

460
00:22:51,908 --> 00:22:54,037
Look, we're gonna be safe.

461
00:22:54,037 --> 00:22:55,540
‐ How do you know?

462
00:22:55,540 --> 00:22:57,168
‐ Because this is the
Capital Banshee,

463
00:22:57,168 --> 00:22:59,882
and we also have
plenty of shelters.

464
00:22:59,882 --> 00:23:00,717
Trust me.

465
00:23:00,717 --> 00:23:01,803
Don't worry, okay?

466
00:23:01,803 --> 00:23:04,474
Federation forces will show up
any moment to help.

467
00:23:04,474 --> 00:23:05,769
‐ You think so?

468
00:23:05,769 --> 00:23:07,898
I sure hope you're right.

469
00:23:07,898 --> 00:23:10,737
[engines running]

470
00:23:19,045 --> 00:23:20,924
‐ [Man] Heat resistant
coating application,

471
00:23:20,924 --> 00:23:22,511
proceeding as planned.

472
00:23:22,511 --> 00:23:23,345
‐ [Man] Pick up the pace.

473
00:23:23,345 --> 00:23:25,433
You're moving too slowly.

474
00:23:29,900 --> 00:23:31,194
‐ What are they up to?

475
00:23:31,194 --> 00:23:33,240
Zeon are maniacs.

476
00:23:33,240 --> 00:23:34,535
‐ They're probably doing
that to keep us

477
00:23:34,535 --> 00:23:36,121
from seeing what's happening.

478
00:23:36,121 --> 00:23:37,290
‐ The bastards,

479
00:23:37,290 --> 00:23:38,375
if they're gonna come at us,

480
00:23:38,375 --> 00:23:40,296
the sooner, the better.

481
00:23:48,688 --> 00:23:51,443
‐ Hey, shouldn't you get going

482
00:23:51,443 --> 00:23:53,322
to the docking bay?

483
00:23:53,322 --> 00:23:55,242
‐ Nah, it's fine.

484
00:23:55,242 --> 00:23:56,829
I plan on staying to
guard the shelter

485
00:23:56,829 --> 00:23:59,668
you and your family
are in anyway.

486
00:24:00,796 --> 00:24:02,591
‐ And do you know how
to use that?

487
00:24:02,591 --> 00:24:04,219
‐ Sure I do.

488
00:24:04,219 --> 00:24:06,516
Easier than playing the guitar.

489
00:24:06,516 --> 00:24:09,479
[murmuring]

490
00:24:09,479 --> 00:24:12,611
‐ Things sure have gotten
really crazy quickly.

491
00:24:12,611 --> 00:24:13,988
Given everything
that's happened,

492
00:24:13,988 --> 00:24:14,907
you would have been better off

493
00:24:14,907 --> 00:24:16,786
if you'd gone to Earth sooner.

494
00:24:16,786 --> 00:24:17,663
‐ I couldn't.

495
00:24:17,663 --> 00:24:19,332
The Yashima Company's
training institute

496
00:24:19,332 --> 00:24:21,128
doesn't open until April.

497
00:24:21,128 --> 00:24:22,338
‐ That's so weird.

498
00:24:22,338 --> 00:24:23,800
‐ What's weird about it?

499
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:26,096
April is cherry blossom
season in Japan.

500
00:24:26,096 --> 00:24:27,348
It's the best time of the year.

501
00:24:27,348 --> 00:24:28,475
‐ You think so?

502
00:24:28,475 --> 00:24:31,440
‐ Actually, I haven't seen
them first hand.

503
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,987
People say falling petals
look like snow.

504
00:24:33,987 --> 00:24:35,782
‐ Like snow.

505
00:24:35,782 --> 00:24:36,576
‐ Guess what?

506
00:24:36,576 --> 00:24:37,410
You probably didn't know,

507
00:24:37,410 --> 00:24:39,999
but I actually have a bit of
Japanese blood in me,

508
00:24:39,999 --> 00:24:42,921
and also snow in
Japanese is yuuki.

509
00:24:43,756 --> 00:24:45,886
‐ Your name means snow.

510
00:24:45,886 --> 00:24:48,056
‐ Not yuki, but yuuki.

511
00:24:48,056 --> 00:24:50,436
My yuki means brave.

512
00:24:50,436 --> 00:24:52,691
[laughing]

513
00:24:52,691 --> 00:24:55,237
That said though, I
do love snow.

514
00:24:55,237 --> 00:24:57,910
‐ I imagine that it must snow
quite a bit in Japan.

515
00:24:57,910 --> 00:24:58,786
Must be nice,

516
00:24:58,786 --> 00:25:00,707
I'd love to go see it sometime.

517
00:25:00,707 --> 00:25:03,838
‐ So let's go as soon
as this is over.

518
00:25:05,466 --> 00:25:07,261
‐ Like together?

519
00:25:07,261 --> 00:25:08,681
‐ Yeah, together.

520
00:25:09,975 --> 00:25:13,650
[gentle instrumental music]

521
00:25:31,644 --> 00:25:33,940
‐ [Man] Heat resistant coating
application complete.

522
00:25:33,940 --> 00:25:36,571
Uprising at docking bay
largely eliminated.

523
00:25:36,571 --> 00:25:39,827
Booster attachment
proceeding smoothly.

524
00:25:41,079 --> 00:25:45,087
[foreboding instrumental music]

525
00:25:48,928 --> 00:25:50,682
‐ Shelter 12 is closing.

526
00:25:50,682 --> 00:25:52,519
Shelter 12 is closing.

527
00:25:54,732 --> 00:25:56,819
‐ Wait for me here, okay?

528
00:26:00,702 --> 00:26:01,537
Stay right there,

529
00:26:01,537 --> 00:26:04,208
and don't go to the docking bay.

530
00:26:07,048 --> 00:26:11,599
[foreboding instrumental music]

531
00:26:11,599 --> 00:26:13,686
‐ [Man] Pumping in the
double G gas.

532
00:26:13,686 --> 00:26:16,651
There's a wind speed of about 10
meters per second inside.

533
00:26:16,651 --> 00:26:20,074
The gas should distribute
rather quickly.

534
00:26:20,992 --> 00:26:23,915
‐ [Man] Elapsed pump time,
five minutes.

535
00:26:23,915 --> 00:26:25,376
‐ It's nothing personal.

536
00:26:25,376 --> 00:26:28,423
We're just trying to put a
swift end to the war.

537
00:26:28,423 --> 00:26:30,344
Besides, I doubt you'd wanna see

538
00:26:30,344 --> 00:26:32,599
the surface of the Earth
rushing toward you.

539
00:26:32,599 --> 00:26:34,687
It'd be too terrifying.

540
00:26:34,687 --> 00:26:38,695
[foreboding instrumental music]

541
00:26:55,687 --> 00:26:57,858
[gasping]

542
00:27:01,448 --> 00:27:03,536
‐ It's so cold.

543
00:27:03,536 --> 00:27:05,372
I'm freezing.

544
00:27:05,372 --> 00:27:08,211
Why is it so cold all
of a sudden?

545
00:27:13,388 --> 00:27:15,100
[gasping]

546
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:17,354
[gentle instrumental music]

547
00:27:17,354 --> 00:27:18,440
It's snowing.

548
00:27:19,358 --> 00:27:22,866
I had no idea that it could
snow in the colonies.

549
00:27:22,866 --> 00:27:24,703
I can't wait to tell Fang Lee.

550
00:27:24,703 --> 00:27:26,289
She'll be thrilled,

551
00:27:28,503 --> 00:27:30,339
but why is it so cold?

552
00:27:32,802 --> 00:27:34,973
[gasping]

553
00:27:37,604 --> 00:27:40,610
[wind blowing]

554
00:27:40,610 --> 00:27:42,154
What happened to them?

555
00:27:42,154 --> 00:27:45,327
That's weird, sleeping
at their posts.

556
00:27:46,664 --> 00:27:48,124
I don't believe it.

557
00:27:48,124 --> 00:27:49,377
It's supposed to be our job

558
00:27:49,377 --> 00:27:51,422
to keep the shelter safe.

559
00:27:53,761 --> 00:27:55,932
[gasping]

560
00:28:00,775 --> 00:28:03,363
[wind blowing]

561
00:28:05,325 --> 00:28:06,912
No, have to get up.

562
00:28:10,587 --> 00:28:12,716
If I fall asleep out here,

563
00:28:16,557 --> 00:28:18,476
then I'll catch a cold.

564
00:28:21,567 --> 00:28:23,278
[grunting]

565
00:28:23,278 --> 00:28:26,284
The shelter, I have to reach it

566
00:28:26,284 --> 00:28:27,537
and get inside.

567
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:37,515
Fang Lee,

568
00:28:40,062 --> 00:28:40,897
open up.

569
00:28:42,066 --> 00:28:43,569
Let me in, please.

570
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:56,135
Let me.

571
00:29:04,611 --> 00:29:05,445
Fang Lee.

572
00:29:14,422 --> 00:29:17,721
[rocket engine running]

573
00:29:19,181 --> 00:29:22,229
‐ [Narrator] Universal
Century 0079,

574
00:29:22,229 --> 00:29:24,568
January 10th, Island Iffish,

575
00:29:25,528 --> 00:29:28,366
Mother Banshee of Side Two,
Hatte,

576
00:29:28,366 --> 00:29:30,203
leaves it's Lagrange Point

577
00:29:30,203 --> 00:29:34,378
and enters into a free fall
trajectory towards Earth.

578
00:29:37,259 --> 00:29:38,846
Its estimated point of impact

579
00:29:38,846 --> 00:29:41,225
was the Guyana Highlands
in South America,

580
00:29:41,225 --> 00:29:42,520
which harbors Jaburo,

581
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:46,360
the Earth Federation's
General HQ, beneath it.

582
00:29:48,072 --> 00:29:50,243
A fleet led by Vice
Admiral Tianum,

583
00:29:50,243 --> 00:29:53,124
which had been en route to
engage the Zeon forces,

584
00:29:53,124 --> 00:29:55,505
abruptly changes its
mission objective.

585
00:29:55,505 --> 00:29:57,550
It attempts to
destroy the colony,

586
00:29:57,550 --> 00:29:59,220
but is unsuccessful.

587
00:30:01,767 --> 00:30:05,942
January 15th, Island Iffish
enters into low Earth orbit.

588
00:30:07,737 --> 00:30:11,745
[foreboding instrumental music]

589
00:30:18,341 --> 00:30:21,097
[metal creaking]

590
00:30:36,377 --> 00:30:40,636
January 16th, the Banshee splits
into three chunks,

591
00:30:40,636 --> 00:30:44,519
and each enters the
Earth's atmosphere.

592
00:30:44,519 --> 00:30:48,527
[foreboding instrumental music]

593
00:31:00,927 --> 00:31:03,933
[station exploding]

594
00:31:10,362 --> 00:31:13,284
When Island Iffish makes
impact with Earth,

595
00:31:13,284 --> 00:31:16,499
it causes massive destruction.

596
00:31:16,499 --> 00:31:19,088
The bay section strikes
southern Australia,

597
00:31:19,088 --> 00:31:20,591
eradicating it,

598
00:31:20,591 --> 00:31:22,344
and the enormous land section

599
00:31:22,344 --> 00:31:24,473
that strikes southwestern Canada

600
00:31:24,473 --> 00:31:26,352
causes debris to rain down

601
00:31:26,352 --> 00:31:29,066
across the majority of America.

602
00:31:29,066 --> 00:31:31,070
The section that came
down in the Pacific

603
00:31:31,070 --> 00:31:33,449
triggers massive
earthquakes and tsunamis

604
00:31:33,449 --> 00:31:35,997
in densely populated East Asia.

605
00:31:37,290 --> 00:31:39,003
[thunder crackling]

606
00:31:39,003 --> 00:31:40,840
The Earth's crust and atmosphere

607
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:43,554
are completely ravaged.

608
00:31:43,554 --> 00:31:46,685
The fatalities from this
terrible calamity are so vast

609
00:31:46,685 --> 00:31:50,233
that its extent is not fully
realized for some time.

610
00:31:50,233 --> 00:31:52,070
When the deaths from
secondary causes

611
00:31:52,070 --> 00:31:55,578
such as disease and starvation
are factored into the tally,

612
00:31:55,578 --> 00:31:57,665
it's clear that the final
number of casualties

613
00:31:57,665 --> 00:32:00,378
is much greater than anyone
could have imagined.

614
00:32:00,378 --> 00:32:03,342
It is roughly half of the
world's population.

615
00:32:03,342 --> 00:32:05,430
However, this is not the end.

616
00:32:05,430 --> 00:32:07,769
The war has only just begun.

617
00:32:08,854 --> 00:32:12,695
[dramatic instrumental music]

618
00:32:16,620 --> 00:32:18,665
‐ The most pressing matter
that we must deal with

619
00:32:18,665 --> 00:32:23,007
at the moment is how to deal
with Side Five, Loum.

620
00:32:23,007 --> 00:32:25,345
The sentiment at Loum
is still split

621
00:32:25,345 --> 00:32:28,727
between siding with us or
standing with the Federation.

622
00:32:28,727 --> 00:32:30,689
The situation
differs from Hatte,

623
00:32:30,689 --> 00:32:32,275
because unlike them,

624
00:32:32,275 --> 00:32:35,073
Loum has already been promised
strong military support

625
00:32:35,073 --> 00:32:37,703
from the Federation government.

626
00:32:37,703 --> 00:32:41,293
The Tianum fleet, the most
powerful fleet in the EFSF,

627
00:32:41,293 --> 00:32:43,297
is already en route to Miranda.

628
00:32:43,297 --> 00:32:45,426
These detail has had a
major influence

629
00:32:45,426 --> 00:32:47,472
on the public opinion there,

630
00:32:47,472 --> 00:32:48,809
and the parties opposed to us

631
00:32:48,809 --> 00:32:51,565
have gained the
upper hand there.

632
00:32:52,942 --> 00:32:56,741
It's clear we've no choice
but to purge Loum.

633
00:32:56,741 --> 00:32:59,121
If we're to win this holy war,

634
00:32:59,121 --> 00:33:03,004
then Loum will play a
crucial role in it.

635
00:33:03,004 --> 00:33:06,636
‐ You already have the blood of
billions on your hands.

636
00:33:06,636 --> 00:33:08,347
How much more blood
must be spilled

637
00:33:08,347 --> 00:33:11,395
before your thirst
will be quenched?

638
00:33:11,395 --> 00:33:13,107
‐ The number that we've killed,

639
00:33:13,107 --> 00:33:15,403
no, rather how many have died,

640
00:33:15,403 --> 00:33:17,115
is of no consequence.

641
00:33:17,115 --> 00:33:19,787
All that matters is that we
vanquish our enemy,

642
00:33:19,787 --> 00:33:21,875
given that Jaburo still stands

643
00:33:21,875 --> 00:33:24,004
and that the Federation
doesn't show any sign

644
00:33:24,004 --> 00:33:25,758
of submitting to our demands.

645
00:33:25,758 --> 00:33:27,344
‐ [Degwin] Whose fault is that?

646
00:33:27,344 --> 00:33:31,519
Isn't this the consequence of
our own failed plan?

647
00:33:31,519 --> 00:33:33,231
‐ The man who led
Operation British

648
00:33:33,231 --> 00:33:35,569
will of course be
punished severely,

649
00:33:35,569 --> 00:33:36,988
and the one who supervised it

650
00:33:36,988 --> 00:33:40,161
will also be held accountable.

651
00:33:40,161 --> 00:33:42,290
‐ In case I wasn't clear,

652
00:33:42,290 --> 00:33:44,504
the one who came up with
this failed plan

653
00:33:44,504 --> 00:33:46,716
and the one who's at
fault is you.

654
00:33:46,716 --> 00:33:48,010
‐ If we emerge victorious,

655
00:33:48,010 --> 00:33:49,973
then none of this will matter.

656
00:33:49,973 --> 00:33:51,433
I assume that you
all do not wish

657
00:33:51,433 --> 00:33:54,147
to be prosecuted as
war criminals.

658
00:33:54,147 --> 00:33:56,277
Then you should put
your faith in me.

659
00:33:56,277 --> 00:33:57,655
I am the man best suited

660
00:33:57,655 --> 00:33:59,408
to provide us with the
leadership we need

661
00:33:59,408 --> 00:34:00,744
to win this war.

662
00:34:04,919 --> 00:34:07,424
‐ I'm returning to my chambers.

663
00:34:07,424 --> 00:34:10,471
Garma, if you would
please accompany me.

664
00:34:10,471 --> 00:34:11,307
‐ Yes.

665
00:34:14,146 --> 00:34:18,237
‐ Too bad, he's getting on in
years, dear father.

666
00:34:19,699 --> 00:34:21,953
[growling]

667
00:34:26,086 --> 00:34:29,259
‐ Zena, Maneva, where are you?

668
00:34:29,259 --> 00:34:30,512
I'm back.

669
00:34:30,512 --> 00:34:33,267
Are my two girls still awake?

670
00:34:33,267 --> 00:34:34,353
Zena, Maneva,

671
00:34:35,647 --> 00:34:38,402
oh, Maneva, you
waited up for me.

672
00:34:40,281 --> 00:34:42,912
Pretty girl, oh how
I missed you.

673
00:34:42,912 --> 00:34:44,957
[baby crying]

674
00:34:44,957 --> 00:34:47,253
Oh, you opened up your eyes.

675
00:34:47,253 --> 00:34:48,673
Your papa's here.

676
00:34:48,673 --> 00:34:49,509
That's right.

677
00:34:49,509 --> 00:34:50,803
I'm your daddy.

678
00:34:50,803 --> 00:34:51,930
Who am I?

679
00:34:51,930 --> 00:34:55,562
Your daddy. [laughing]

680
00:34:55,562 --> 00:34:58,067
[baby crying]

681
00:35:01,866 --> 00:35:04,831
‐ Oh, there, there, did
you get scared?

682
00:35:04,831 --> 00:35:07,168
Your daddy can be so naughty.

683
00:35:07,168 --> 00:35:09,674
[baby crying]

684
00:35:12,763 --> 00:35:14,391
‐ [Dozle] Is she asleep?

685
00:35:14,391 --> 00:35:16,688
‐ Yes, she's asleep.

686
00:35:16,688 --> 00:35:18,608
We played together all day long.

687
00:35:18,608 --> 00:35:21,113
I think it tires her out.

688
00:35:21,113 --> 00:35:22,700
‐ Aw, how adorable.

689
00:35:25,581 --> 00:35:26,916
Maneva's so previous.

690
00:35:26,916 --> 00:35:30,256
I couldn't bear if something
happened to her.

691
00:35:30,256 --> 00:35:33,513
What have I, [crying].

692
00:35:35,517 --> 00:35:39,984
Just how many millions of little
Maneva's have perished

693
00:35:39,984 --> 00:35:42,197
all because of me?

694
00:35:42,197 --> 00:35:44,284
[crying]

695
00:35:47,290 --> 00:35:50,964
[gentle instrumental music]

696
00:35:56,518 --> 00:36:00,191
Maneva started crying the
instant she saw my face.

697
00:36:00,191 --> 00:36:03,573
Does my face look
that terrifying?

698
00:36:03,573 --> 00:36:05,953
I guess I must have the
face of the devil

699
00:36:05,953 --> 00:36:06,871
or an ogre.

700
00:36:07,790 --> 00:36:10,211
Yes, that must be it.

701
00:36:10,211 --> 00:36:11,923
‐ Don't be silly, my dear.

702
00:36:11,923 --> 00:36:13,844
She was cranky because
she was sleepy.

703
00:36:13,844 --> 00:36:15,597
There's no need to read into it.

704
00:36:15,597 --> 00:36:17,267
‐ Do you think so?

705
00:36:17,267 --> 00:36:19,814
Is that why she was crying?

706
00:36:19,814 --> 00:36:22,611
I hope that you're right.

707
00:36:22,611 --> 00:36:25,993
You know, I like my family the
way it was before

708
00:36:25,993 --> 00:36:27,955
back when we all lived
together in this house

709
00:36:27,955 --> 00:36:29,584
and when we got along.

710
00:36:29,584 --> 00:36:31,504
Sasura was still alive,

711
00:36:31,504 --> 00:36:33,967
and Garma was just a tiny
kid and so cute.

712
00:36:33,967 --> 00:36:37,140
Well, I guess Garma's
still really cute.

713
00:36:37,140 --> 00:36:39,477
[grunting]

714
00:36:39,477 --> 00:36:40,313
Zena,

715
00:36:42,317 --> 00:36:44,279
I am going to make it
my personal goal

716
00:36:44,279 --> 00:36:45,699
to make sure that you
don't regret

717
00:36:45,699 --> 00:36:47,828
marrying into the Zabi family.

718
00:36:47,828 --> 00:36:49,247
You and I together,

719
00:36:49,247 --> 00:36:52,420
we can create a new
legacy for the Zabis.

720
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:54,592
I want you to bear me
lots of children,

721
00:36:54,592 --> 00:36:57,723
brothers for Maneva
and sisters too.

722
00:36:57,723 --> 00:37:00,061
We'll make plenty of good
little children,

723
00:37:00,061 --> 00:37:01,981
and I swear I will
keep them safe,

724
00:37:01,981 --> 00:37:04,277
every single one of them.

725
00:37:04,277 --> 00:37:06,156
[murmuring]

726
00:37:06,156 --> 00:37:08,452
Anyone who lays a hand
on you or Maneva

727
00:37:08,452 --> 00:37:11,960
will answer to me, no
matter who they are.

728
00:37:13,170 --> 00:37:14,548
I get it now.

729
00:37:14,548 --> 00:37:17,638
This is the reason men fight,
see?

730
00:37:17,638 --> 00:37:19,767
When you have people
that you love,

731
00:37:19,767 --> 00:37:21,896
you have no choice but to fight.

732
00:37:21,896 --> 00:37:24,067
Those fools living in Hatte,

733
00:37:24,067 --> 00:37:26,488
and the same can be said
for the Federation,

734
00:37:26,488 --> 00:37:30,539
they were too weak to keep
their Manevas safe,

735
00:37:30,539 --> 00:37:32,375
so it was their fault.

736
00:37:33,837 --> 00:37:35,799
I am not weak like them.

737
00:37:37,468 --> 00:37:40,474
I will crush every
single one of them.

738
00:37:40,474 --> 00:37:42,688
If they dare touch
Maneva and Zena,

739
00:37:42,688 --> 00:37:44,817
I'll rip them in half,

740
00:37:44,817 --> 00:37:46,821
on this I swear, dammit.

741
00:37:48,700 --> 00:37:51,204
[baby crying]

742
00:37:52,583 --> 00:37:55,337
‐ Oh no, she's awake again.

743
00:37:55,337 --> 00:37:57,551
[baby crying]

744
00:37:57,551 --> 00:37:59,597
There, there, you poor thing,

745
00:37:59,597 --> 00:38:02,477
I'm afraid your daddy just
loves to shout so.

746
00:38:02,477 --> 00:38:04,105
Oh, oh.

747
00:38:04,105 --> 00:38:05,066
‐ I'm sorry.

748
00:38:05,066 --> 00:38:05,901
‐ Oh, oh.

749
00:38:11,244 --> 00:38:13,165
[dramatic instrumental music]

750
00:38:13,165 --> 00:38:15,921
[crowd chanting]

751
00:38:36,336 --> 00:38:39,259
[metal clattering]

752
00:38:41,221 --> 00:38:43,810
‐ [Reporter] The military has
mobilized to keep the peace.

753
00:38:43,810 --> 00:38:46,774
They're opening fire on the
pro‐Zeon protestors.

754
00:38:46,774 --> 00:38:48,570
The Loum government appears
to have hardened

755
00:38:48,570 --> 00:38:50,239
its anti‐Zeon position

756
00:38:50,239 --> 00:38:53,538
and has the full backing of the
Federation military.

757
00:38:53,538 --> 00:38:56,669
[siren ringing]

758
00:38:56,669 --> 00:38:58,590
‐ [Doctor] No, we can't accept
any more patients.

759
00:38:58,590 --> 00:39:00,009
‐ Send the injured to
another hospital.

760
00:39:00,009 --> 00:39:03,015
‐ Doctor, this kid is
hurt real bad.

761
00:39:05,729 --> 00:39:08,442
‐ Please, you can't let him die.

762
00:39:08,442 --> 00:39:10,237
[yelling]

763
00:39:10,237 --> 00:39:12,241
‐ I'll do what I can
to treat him.

764
00:39:12,241 --> 00:39:15,582
Please, move him to the
sofa over there.

765
00:39:16,709 --> 00:39:19,506
‐ You're Miss Artesia,
aren't you?

766
00:39:20,592 --> 00:39:21,928
‐ I'm sorry.

767
00:39:21,928 --> 00:39:23,388
You're mistaken.

768
00:39:23,388 --> 00:39:26,311
‐ Before you go, my
identification.

769
00:39:29,275 --> 00:39:30,862
Might you consider giving
me a few minutes

770
00:39:30,862 --> 00:39:32,824
of your time now?

771
00:39:32,824 --> 00:39:35,454
[helicopter engine running]

772
00:39:35,454 --> 00:39:38,168
‐ What did you want to speak to
me about, Lieutenant Tachi?

773
00:39:38,168 --> 00:39:39,588
I've got to admit to you,

774
00:39:39,588 --> 00:39:40,799
you are an odd one.

775
00:39:40,799 --> 00:39:42,426
I've never had an
intelligence operative

776
00:39:42,426 --> 00:39:44,264
show me his ID before.

777
00:39:46,268 --> 00:39:49,482
‐ Long time no see,
Lady Artesia.

778
00:39:49,482 --> 00:39:50,527
I don't know if you're aware,

779
00:39:50,527 --> 00:39:52,531
but when you and your
brother escaped Munzo,

780
00:39:52,531 --> 00:39:55,620
I played a
significant part in it,

781
00:39:55,620 --> 00:39:56,914
although in truth,

782
00:39:56,914 --> 00:39:59,168
the only thing I did was follow
Mr. Ral's instructions

783
00:39:59,168 --> 00:40:02,551
on how to get you and your
party past customs.

784
00:40:02,551 --> 00:40:03,720
‐ I would really appreciate it

785
00:40:03,720 --> 00:40:05,974
if you would just stop
beating around the bush.

786
00:40:05,974 --> 00:40:07,644
It's not that I'm not
interested in hearing

787
00:40:07,644 --> 00:40:09,022
what you have to say,

788
00:40:09,022 --> 00:40:10,232
but it isn't a good time.

789
00:40:10,232 --> 00:40:12,320
A lot is happening right now.

790
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:13,405
‐ I'm well aware of that.

791
00:40:13,405 --> 00:40:15,075
It's the reason why
I'm even here.

792
00:40:15,075 --> 00:40:17,038
You see, I wouldn't have been
able to have made contact

793
00:40:17,038 --> 00:40:19,585
if it weren't for the current
state of affairs.

794
00:40:19,585 --> 00:40:21,046
Believe me, it's no easy task

795
00:40:21,046 --> 00:40:23,300
to beat the Kycilia
Agency to the punch,

796
00:40:23,300 --> 00:40:26,306
intelligence operative or not.

797
00:40:26,306 --> 00:40:27,726
Now you're familiar with a man

798
00:40:27,726 --> 00:40:30,648
named Char Aznable, aren't you?

799
00:40:30,648 --> 00:40:31,483
‐ What?

800
00:40:31,483 --> 00:40:32,318
Char?

801
00:40:32,318 --> 00:40:34,782
[helicopter engine running]

802
00:40:34,782 --> 00:40:38,455
[gentle instrumental music]

803
00:40:41,837 --> 00:40:42,839
What is it?

804
00:40:42,839 --> 00:40:44,593
What is this all about?

805
00:40:44,593 --> 00:40:47,181
‐ I first took note when he was
expelled from the academy

806
00:40:47,181 --> 00:40:49,310
for inciting the cadet uprising,

807
00:40:49,310 --> 00:40:51,314
and since then, he's made a
name for himself

808
00:40:51,314 --> 00:40:53,360
as the pilot of a red
Mobile Suit.

809
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:55,615
He's now a young hero of Zeon,

810
00:40:55,615 --> 00:40:59,497
and he's risen from enlisted
man to lieutenant.

811
00:41:00,583 --> 00:41:04,382
I suggest that you keep a
close eye on him.

812
00:41:04,382 --> 00:41:07,889
‐ What exactly are you
trying to say?

813
00:41:07,889 --> 00:41:09,893
‐ I have one other piece
of information.

814
00:41:09,893 --> 00:41:12,273
It's about Casval Rem Deikun.

815
00:41:12,273 --> 00:41:13,985
He's still alive.

816
00:41:13,985 --> 00:41:16,156
[gasping]

817
00:41:17,951 --> 00:41:19,120
[metal clattering]

818
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:21,249
Although to be perfectly honest,

819
00:41:21,249 --> 00:41:22,293
all of this is just based

820
00:41:22,293 --> 00:41:23,713
on my personal opinion.

821
00:41:23,713 --> 00:41:25,592
‐ No, please wait.

822
00:41:25,592 --> 00:41:27,386
‐ Sorry I can't stay longer.

823
00:41:27,386 --> 00:41:28,931
If anyone here found
out I was Zeon,

824
00:41:28,931 --> 00:41:31,394
they'd string me up for sure.

825
00:41:31,394 --> 00:41:32,939
‐ Lieutenant Tachi, wait.

826
00:41:32,939 --> 00:41:35,820
[electronic ringing]

827
00:41:35,820 --> 00:41:37,156
Yes, hello?

828
00:41:37,156 --> 00:41:38,659
Don't worry, I'll,

829
00:41:39,912 --> 00:41:41,707
Mr. Aznable?

830
00:41:41,707 --> 00:41:43,168
‐ [Roger] Sayla, it's me.

831
00:41:43,168 --> 00:41:45,214
Mr. Teabolo's collapsed.

832
00:41:45,214 --> 00:41:46,967
They say it was a heart attack.

833
00:41:46,967 --> 00:41:50,349
Could you come home immediately?

834
00:41:50,349 --> 00:41:51,226
Hello?

835
00:41:51,226 --> 00:41:52,061
Sayla?

836
00:41:53,146 --> 00:41:55,317
Can you hear me?

837
00:41:55,317 --> 00:41:56,862
Hello?

838
00:41:56,862 --> 00:41:58,574
Are you still there?

839
00:41:58,574 --> 00:42:00,620
This is Roger Aznable.

840
00:42:00,620 --> 00:42:01,956
Hello?

841
00:42:01,956 --> 00:42:05,630
[helicopter engine running]

842
00:42:11,559 --> 00:42:14,021
‐ [Man] Pilot inspection,
proceed to test mode.

843
00:42:14,021 --> 00:42:15,942
‐ [Man] L Three gauge
isn't climbing.

844
00:42:15,942 --> 00:42:17,069
‐ [Man] Start with L Five‐‐

845
00:42:17,069 --> 00:42:18,280
‐ We're in the process right now

846
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:20,827
of attaching stronger
thrusters to the packs,

847
00:42:20,827 --> 00:42:22,288
and the nozzle's range of motion

848
00:42:22,288 --> 00:42:24,375
is now 50% greater.

849
00:42:24,375 --> 00:42:26,714
We're also attaching
custom fins.

850
00:42:26,714 --> 00:42:28,593
‐ Woah, not too shabby.

851
00:42:29,678 --> 00:42:32,642
These new Zaku models are not
too shabby at all.

852
00:42:32,642 --> 00:42:33,978
Now that's the kind of machine

853
00:42:33,978 --> 00:42:36,232
worthy of us Black Tri‐Stars.

854
00:42:36,232 --> 00:42:38,028
‐ I particularly like that star.

855
00:42:38,028 --> 00:42:41,075
‐ [murmuring] After all, the
way you look fighting

856
00:42:41,075 --> 00:42:44,123
is just as important as
the fight itself.

857
00:42:44,123 --> 00:42:47,212
[murmuring]

858
00:42:47,212 --> 00:42:48,841
[suit engine running]

859
00:42:48,841 --> 00:42:51,722
‐ Hey guys, what was that?

860
00:42:51,722 --> 00:42:54,895
[suit engine running]

861
00:43:02,744 --> 00:43:05,415
[siren ringing]

862
00:43:07,754 --> 00:43:10,217
‐ What's with that flashy horn?

863
00:43:10,217 --> 00:43:11,512
He wants his to be red

864
00:43:11,512 --> 00:43:13,348
because he wants to
deliberately stand out

865
00:43:13,348 --> 00:43:14,851
from the rest of us.

866
00:43:14,851 --> 00:43:17,481
Nobody else would make such
a request but him.

867
00:43:17,481 --> 00:43:20,028
Why's he gotta be so obnoxious?

868
00:43:23,201 --> 00:43:24,579
Told you so, see?

869
00:43:24,579 --> 00:43:26,165
I was right.

870
00:43:26,165 --> 00:43:29,422
‐ Mechanic, I'm currently only
getting 80% output

871
00:43:29,422 --> 00:43:31,342
from the sub thrusters.

872
00:43:33,764 --> 00:43:35,518
I don't believe that's
the response level

873
00:43:35,518 --> 00:43:37,271
I requested, correct?

874
00:43:38,858 --> 00:43:40,737
‐ Considering the
stress on the pilot,

875
00:43:40,737 --> 00:43:43,158
we thought it would be best to
have a limiter installed.

876
00:43:43,158 --> 00:43:43,993
‐ Remove it.

877
00:43:43,993 --> 00:43:44,828
I don't need it.

878
00:43:44,828 --> 00:43:48,753
‐ Hey, asshole. [growling]

879
00:43:48,753 --> 00:43:51,592
‐ Oh, are you here for your
inspections as well?

880
00:43:51,592 --> 00:43:54,931
Couldn't wait for your
customized machines, huh?

881
00:43:54,931 --> 00:43:57,019
[yelling]

882
00:43:57,019 --> 00:43:59,482
‐ Lieutenant Char, I suppose
I outta give you

883
00:43:59,482 --> 00:44:02,362
my congratulations for
another promotion.

884
00:44:02,362 --> 00:44:05,368
‐ A rather swift double pump
promotion at that,

885
00:44:05,368 --> 00:44:07,749
while Commander Ral was
demoted to lieutenant

886
00:44:07,749 --> 00:44:10,003
in the reserves too.

887
00:44:10,003 --> 00:44:14,136
‐ That officer's uniform suits
you, Lieutenant Junior Grade.

888
00:44:14,136 --> 00:44:16,642
There's just one
thing about that.

889
00:44:16,642 --> 00:44:18,854
Not wearing a normal suit
while piloting that

890
00:44:18,854 --> 00:44:20,190
is against regs.

891
00:44:21,192 --> 00:44:25,576
‐ Lieutenant, if the suit I'm
piloting is destroyed,

892
00:44:25,576 --> 00:44:30,545
I'll be just as dead regardless
of what I'm wearing.

893
00:44:30,545 --> 00:44:32,130
I'm going back out.

894
00:44:33,049 --> 00:44:35,178
I had no idea you three paid
so much attention

895
00:44:35,178 --> 00:44:37,057
to one's promotions.

896
00:44:37,057 --> 00:44:38,644
If you're looking to
climb up the ranks,

897
00:44:38,644 --> 00:44:43,027
then you've got to actually
accomplish something.

898
00:44:43,027 --> 00:44:45,992
All eyes will be on the
battle at Loum.

899
00:44:45,992 --> 00:44:47,745
It could the
opportunity of a lifetime

900
00:44:47,745 --> 00:44:48,914
for you three.

901
00:44:50,041 --> 00:44:52,589
We can compete to see which of
us performs the best.

902
00:44:52,589 --> 00:44:54,091
So long, Tri‐Stars.

903
00:44:54,091 --> 00:44:57,389
I will see you on the
battlefield.

904
00:44:57,389 --> 00:45:01,397
[foreboding instrumental music]

905
00:45:05,865 --> 00:45:09,163
‐ [Reporter] We are coming to
you live from Miranda Bay.

906
00:45:09,163 --> 00:45:11,710
The exodus of pro‐Zeon
citizens continues

907
00:45:11,710 --> 00:45:13,212
amidst a state of high alert

908
00:45:13,212 --> 00:45:15,383
issued by the
military and police.

909
00:45:15,383 --> 00:45:16,762
It now seems inevitable

910
00:45:16,762 --> 00:45:20,895
that the Loum region will become
the next battlefield.

911
00:45:20,895 --> 00:45:21,939
The tragedy of Hatte,

912
00:45:21,939 --> 00:45:24,068
who's Capital Banshee was
dropped on Earth,

913
00:45:24,068 --> 00:45:26,782
is causing widespread
panic on all parts.

914
00:45:26,782 --> 00:45:30,623
[dramatic instrumental music]

915
00:45:38,012 --> 00:45:40,350
‐ He seems to be in
stable condition now,

916
00:45:40,350 --> 00:45:42,814
and since you've managed to make
it safely back here,

917
00:45:42,814 --> 00:45:45,443
I think we can all rest
a bit easier.

918
00:45:45,443 --> 00:45:47,782
[murmuring]

919
00:45:49,995 --> 00:45:50,997
[insects chirping]

920
00:45:50,997 --> 00:45:51,832
‐ [Sayla] What?

921
00:45:51,832 --> 00:45:53,627
You're moving to Zeon?

922
00:45:53,627 --> 00:45:54,504
‐ If we stay here,

923
00:45:54,504 --> 00:45:56,717
there's no telling what
danger we may face

924
00:45:56,717 --> 00:45:59,471
since we're citizens of
an enemy country.

925
00:45:59,471 --> 00:46:01,100
I'd like to relocate to Zeon

926
00:46:01,100 --> 00:46:03,354
while they're still
offering flights there,

927
00:46:03,354 --> 00:46:04,816
and besides‐‐

928
00:46:04,816 --> 00:46:06,277
‐ Besides what?

929
00:46:06,277 --> 00:46:08,991
‐ Well, it has to do with Char,
obviously.

930
00:46:08,991 --> 00:46:10,911
[gasping]

931
00:46:10,911 --> 00:46:12,832
I'm not at all interested
in seeing the man

932
00:46:12,832 --> 00:46:15,546
who's suddenly become
the hero of Zeon,

933
00:46:15,546 --> 00:46:18,844
but even if he hasn't written
us a single letter,

934
00:46:18,844 --> 00:46:19,929
the truth of the matter is

935
00:46:19,929 --> 00:46:22,602
he's still the only son we have.

936
00:46:23,771 --> 00:46:25,190
‐ I understand you.

937
00:46:25,190 --> 00:46:27,194
I know how you must feel.

938
00:46:27,194 --> 00:46:29,532
‐ I'm sorry for
springing this on you.

939
00:46:29,532 --> 00:46:32,872
I know this is probably
terrible timing right now.

940
00:46:32,872 --> 00:46:35,920
‐ No, that's quite alright, Mr.
Aznable.

941
00:46:35,920 --> 00:46:37,799
Please, don't you
worry about it.

942
00:46:37,799 --> 00:46:39,886
You've done so much for us
over the years,

943
00:46:39,886 --> 00:46:42,015
and I'm grateful for all of it.

944
00:46:42,015 --> 00:46:45,856
‐ Thank you so much
for saying that.

945
00:46:45,856 --> 00:46:48,946
Having you in our lives was
a great pleasure.

946
00:46:48,946 --> 00:46:52,369
I have faith that one day our
paths will cross again.

947
00:46:52,369 --> 00:46:56,377
[foreboding instrumental music]

948
00:47:10,071 --> 00:47:12,994
[insects chirping]

949
00:47:20,091 --> 00:47:21,553
‐ Oh, Casval.

950
00:47:21,553 --> 00:47:24,976
‐ You're familiar with a man
named Char Aznable, aren't you?

951
00:47:24,976 --> 00:47:29,569
You're familiar with a man named
Char Aznable, aren't you?

952
00:47:29,569 --> 00:47:31,823
It's about Casval Rem Deikun.

953
00:47:31,823 --> 00:47:33,660
He's still alive.

954
00:47:33,660 --> 00:47:35,581
It's about Casval Rem Deikun.

955
00:47:35,581 --> 00:47:37,000
He's still alive.

956
00:47:40,966 --> 00:47:44,139
‐ [Sayla] Casval, what happened?

957
00:47:44,139 --> 00:47:46,937
What did you do to
that poor boy?

958
00:47:46,937 --> 00:47:50,276
[rocket engine running]

959
00:47:59,294 --> 00:48:03,219
[foreboding instrumental music]

960
00:48:23,593 --> 00:48:26,558
‐ [Narrator] Universal
Century 0079,

961
00:48:26,558 --> 00:48:27,643
January 23rd,

962
00:48:29,146 --> 00:48:31,317
the EFSF's third fleet

963
00:48:31,317 --> 00:48:34,239
launched from the newly
constructed Jaburo base

964
00:48:34,239 --> 00:48:37,162
and rendezvoused with Admiral
Reval's first fleet,

965
00:48:37,162 --> 00:48:40,794
which had been on standby in
the Luna Two area.

966
00:48:40,794 --> 00:48:44,217
From there, it immediately set
out for the Loum region

967
00:48:44,217 --> 00:48:47,390
located on the opposite
side of Earth.

968
00:48:47,390 --> 00:48:49,520
With this force that
vastly outnumbered

969
00:48:49,520 --> 00:48:51,566
the combined Zeon forces,

970
00:48:51,566 --> 00:48:56,116
the Federation intended to
settle the war in one blow.

971
00:48:56,116 --> 00:49:00,083
[foreboding instrumental music]

972
00:49:12,107 --> 00:49:16,658
‐ A battle at Loum will decide
the outcome of the war,

973
00:49:16,658 --> 00:49:19,037
or rather, it must decide it.

974
00:49:19,037 --> 00:49:20,958
Steel your resolve, gentlemen.

975
00:49:20,958 --> 00:49:24,381
I expect that the EFSF is
burning with desire

976
00:49:24,381 --> 00:49:25,968
for revenge over the
blow it received

977
00:49:25,968 --> 00:49:28,097
from Operation British.

978
00:49:28,097 --> 00:49:32,480
Therefore, we mustn't
underestimate its will to fight.

979
00:49:32,480 --> 00:49:35,529
Only by uniting our forces
under our sovereign

980
00:49:35,529 --> 00:49:38,367
and putting the very fate of our
principality on the line

981
00:49:38,367 --> 00:49:41,081
will our victory be possible.

982
00:49:41,081 --> 00:49:43,294
Now then, on to the briefing.

983
00:49:43,294 --> 00:49:46,885
Vice Admiral Dozle, you now
have the floor.

984
00:49:50,517 --> 00:49:52,312
‐ Let us not forget.

985
00:49:52,312 --> 00:49:54,650
Every one of us is a
war criminal.

986
00:49:54,650 --> 00:49:58,032
Should we fail, it will be
the gallows for us.

987
00:49:58,032 --> 00:50:00,369
[murmuring]

988
00:50:03,877 --> 00:50:06,298
The enemy's forces are
split in two.

989
00:50:06,298 --> 00:50:08,512
One of them, led by Vice
Admiral Tianum,

990
00:50:08,512 --> 00:50:10,933
is currently hovering
near the Loum area,

991
00:50:10,933 --> 00:50:14,231
composed of 15 Magellan
class battleships,

992
00:50:14,231 --> 00:50:17,403
also 45 Salamis class cruisers,

993
00:50:17,403 --> 00:50:19,992
as well as Lepanto class
missile frigates,

994
00:50:19,992 --> 00:50:21,788
landing crafts and the usual.

995
00:50:21,788 --> 00:50:25,336
This fleet alone is comparable
to our entire force.

996
00:50:25,336 --> 00:50:26,714
[murmuring]

997
00:50:26,714 --> 00:50:29,762
Furthermore, Reval's main force
will be joining them,

998
00:50:29,762 --> 00:50:32,225
and this fleet will
probably be three times

999
00:50:32,225 --> 00:50:34,814
the size of Tianum's,
a real armada.

1000
00:50:34,814 --> 00:50:37,695
‐ A force four times our size?

1001
00:50:37,695 --> 00:50:39,907
‐ That's right, four
times larger.

1002
00:50:39,907 --> 00:50:40,951
Nothing can be done about

1003
00:50:40,951 --> 00:50:42,705
the difference in
fighting strength,

1004
00:50:42,705 --> 00:50:45,836
so that's why we will not
be implementing

1005
00:50:45,836 --> 00:50:47,881
some ineffective plan to
divide our force

1006
00:50:47,881 --> 00:50:49,844
into smaller ones to
attack them.

1007
00:50:49,844 --> 00:50:52,390
Instead, we are going to hit
the Tianum fleet

1008
00:50:52,390 --> 00:50:54,394
with everything we have.

1009
00:50:55,271 --> 00:50:57,358
[laughing]

1010
00:50:57,358 --> 00:50:58,945
‐ Wait, and what do
you intend to do

1011
00:50:58,945 --> 00:51:00,699
about Reval's main force?

1012
00:51:00,699 --> 00:51:01,868
‐ Don't worry.

1013
00:51:01,868 --> 00:51:03,495
We will hit Reval's force

1014
00:51:03,495 --> 00:51:05,249
with a Special Assault Regiment

1015
00:51:05,249 --> 00:51:09,090
launched from [murmuring].

1016
00:51:09,090 --> 00:51:10,886
‐ A Special Assault Regiment?

1017
00:51:10,886 --> 00:51:12,055
Wait a second.

1018
00:51:12,055 --> 00:51:12,931
‐ I'm sorry.

1019
00:51:12,931 --> 00:51:13,975
What's that?

1020
00:51:13,975 --> 00:51:16,564
‐ I know that you generals are
unfamiliar with it,

1021
00:51:16,564 --> 00:51:18,777
but the unit has
already proven itself

1022
00:51:18,777 --> 00:51:20,947
more than capable in battle.

1023
00:51:20,947 --> 00:51:21,824
For this mission,

1024
00:51:21,824 --> 00:51:24,496
I'll organize it into
two battalions,

1025
00:51:24,496 --> 00:51:26,249
and the fleet led by Reval

1026
00:51:26,249 --> 00:51:28,337
won't know what hit them.

1027
00:51:31,678 --> 00:51:34,224
[crowd chanting]

1028
00:51:34,224 --> 00:51:37,438
‐ [Crowd] Sieg Zeon, Sieg Zeon,

1029
00:51:37,438 --> 00:51:39,192
Sieg Zeon, Sieg Zeon,

1030
00:51:40,779 --> 00:51:42,533
Sieg Zeon, Sieg Zeon,

1031
00:51:44,327 --> 00:51:46,081
Sieg Zeon, Sieg Zeon,

1032
00:51:47,918 --> 00:51:49,672
Sieg Zeon, Sieg Zeon.

1033
00:51:52,636 --> 00:51:53,680
[neon crackling]

1034
00:51:53,680 --> 00:51:54,807
[gentle instrumental music]

1035
00:51:54,807 --> 00:51:56,101
‐ Alright, you two,

1036
00:51:56,101 --> 00:51:57,604
I'll be going now.

1037
00:51:58,857 --> 00:51:59,692
‐ Really?

1038
00:51:59,692 --> 00:52:01,278
You leaving already, Clamp?

1039
00:52:01,278 --> 00:52:02,488
‐ Hey, Commander.

1040
00:52:02,488 --> 00:52:04,117
I mean, Lieutenant.

1041
00:52:04,117 --> 00:52:07,123
‐ Cozun, long time, no see.

1042
00:52:07,123 --> 00:52:07,958
Want a drink?

1043
00:52:07,958 --> 00:52:08,793
Join me.

1044
00:52:08,793 --> 00:52:10,254
‐ Oh, I'd love to, really,

1045
00:52:10,254 --> 00:52:12,133
but I'm afraid the
transport convoy

1046
00:52:12,133 --> 00:52:13,302
is leaving soon.

1047
00:52:13,302 --> 00:52:14,555
‐ And they say that
anybody who's late

1048
00:52:14,555 --> 00:52:18,312
for this critical battle will be
considered unpatriotic.

1049
00:52:18,312 --> 00:52:20,107
‐ They would do that.

1050
00:52:20,107 --> 00:52:22,153
Well, get going then.

1051
00:52:22,153 --> 00:52:23,990
‐ I volunteered in hopes
that I'd be able

1052
00:52:23,990 --> 00:52:26,996
to serve with you again if I
was a Zaku pilot,

1053
00:52:26,996 --> 00:52:29,417
but you had to be selfish,

1054
00:52:29,417 --> 00:52:32,465
and you mustered out already.

1055
00:52:32,465 --> 00:52:34,260
Petty Office Cozun Graham,

1056
00:52:34,260 --> 00:52:37,518
now shipping out to the front
lines of Loum, sir.

1057
00:52:37,518 --> 00:52:41,191
[gentle instrumental music]

1058
00:52:42,569 --> 00:52:44,990
‐ Yeah, yeah, good riddance.

1059
00:52:44,990 --> 00:52:45,992
Don't forget,

1060
00:52:45,992 --> 00:52:49,290
the Zabis are a bunch of no
good murderers.

1061
00:52:49,290 --> 00:52:51,336
There's no need for you to
shed a drop of blood

1062
00:52:51,336 --> 00:52:52,756
for that lot,

1063
00:52:52,756 --> 00:52:53,633
and whatever you do,

1064
00:52:53,633 --> 00:52:55,427
you'd better not die on
their behalf,

1065
00:52:55,427 --> 00:52:56,429
you hear me?

1066
00:52:58,016 --> 00:52:59,520
[neon crackling]

1067
00:52:59,520 --> 00:53:03,193
[gentle instrumental music]

1068
00:53:06,826 --> 00:53:08,997
[snoring]

1069
00:53:13,338 --> 00:53:14,592
‐ Who's there?

1070
00:53:14,592 --> 00:53:15,426
I'm sorry.

1071
00:53:15,426 --> 00:53:17,346
We're closed right now.

1072
00:53:24,319 --> 00:53:27,199
Well, look what the
cat dragged in.

1073
00:53:27,199 --> 00:53:30,205
From what I hear, you're working
in intelligence now.

1074
00:53:30,205 --> 00:53:31,876
‐ I need you to run.

1075
00:53:33,045 --> 00:53:35,174
The Kycilia Agency are
on their way.

1076
00:53:35,174 --> 00:53:36,969
They're going to arrest you
and the Lieutenant

1077
00:53:36,969 --> 00:53:38,556
for insubordination.

1078
00:53:38,556 --> 00:53:40,894
[footsteps]

1079
00:53:46,363 --> 00:53:48,241
‐ We're looking for
Lieutenant Ramba Ral.

1080
00:53:48,241 --> 00:53:49,494
Is he here?

1081
00:53:49,494 --> 00:53:50,705
‐ Ral's in the back,

1082
00:53:50,705 --> 00:53:52,626
but he's sleeping.

1083
00:53:52,626 --> 00:53:53,962
What's this about?

1084
00:53:53,962 --> 00:53:55,632
‐ He refused to obey
a direct order

1085
00:53:55,632 --> 00:53:57,301
during Operation British,

1086
00:53:57,301 --> 00:53:59,765
so an arrest warrant's been
issued for him,

1087
00:53:59,765 --> 00:54:01,769
and if you don't hand
him over to us,

1088
00:54:01,769 --> 00:54:03,271
we'll bring you in too.

1089
00:54:03,271 --> 00:54:05,610
‐ Must I remind you that he's
already been punished

1090
00:54:05,610 --> 00:54:07,446
with a two rank demotion?

1091
00:54:07,446 --> 00:54:10,160
Besides, the direct order that
you are referring to

1092
00:54:10,160 --> 00:54:13,166
was actually issued by
Vice Admiral Dozle,

1093
00:54:13,166 --> 00:54:15,839
and it has nothing to
do with Kycilia.

1094
00:54:15,839 --> 00:54:17,551
So if she wants to arrest him,

1095
00:54:17,551 --> 00:54:20,472
she's going to have to bring the
warrant here herself

1096
00:54:20,472 --> 00:54:22,184
instead of sending out a
group of flunkies

1097
00:54:22,184 --> 00:54:24,188
like you to do her dirty work.

1098
00:54:24,188 --> 00:54:25,817
So if you would,

1099
00:54:25,817 --> 00:54:27,111
please forward her that message

1100
00:54:27,111 --> 00:54:29,992
from a Miss Crowley Hamon.

1101
00:54:29,992 --> 00:54:32,329
[murmuring]

1102
00:54:33,373 --> 00:54:35,545
[snoring]

1103
00:54:41,139 --> 00:54:45,439
[dramatic instrumental music]

1104
00:54:45,439 --> 00:54:49,113
[gentle instrumental music]

1105
00:55:07,233 --> 00:55:09,863
♫ Deep in my mind

1106
00:55:09,863 --> 00:55:13,538
♫ Neon signs shining bright

1107
00:55:14,915 --> 00:55:18,673
♫ Smoke faded into the night

1108
00:55:20,927 --> 00:55:24,016
♫ The doors left ajar

1109
00:55:24,016 --> 00:55:27,439
♫ With a glimmer of hope

1110
00:55:29,026 --> 00:55:32,868
♫ Just so you come back again

1111
00:55:34,538 --> 00:55:37,126
♫ Time goes by

1112
00:55:39,255 --> 00:55:41,384
♫ Goes by

1113
00:55:43,471 --> 00:55:47,229
♫ No matter how hard you try

1114
00:55:48,983 --> 00:55:51,947
♫ Don't say goodbye

1115
00:55:53,116 --> 00:55:55,245
♫ Goodbye

1116
00:55:57,751 --> 00:56:01,926
♫ Now that our story has
come to an end

1117
00:56:03,888 --> 00:56:06,810
♫ Feel your life

1118
00:56:06,810 --> 00:56:10,818
♫ Bursting into flames

1119
00:56:10,818 --> 00:56:14,158
♫ Every day, everywhere

1120
00:56:17,874 --> 00:56:21,214
♫ I believe in eternity

1121
00:56:24,680 --> 00:56:27,978
♫ The stream of time

1122
00:56:27,978 --> 00:56:32,152
♫ Never stops, never
sets me free

1123
00:56:33,990 --> 00:56:37,622
[gentle instrumental music]

1124
00:56:44,845 --> 00:56:47,892
[glass clattering]

1125
00:56:47,892 --> 00:56:51,315
♫ The town's fast asleep

1126
00:56:51,315 --> 00:56:55,115
♫ It's asleep dreaming of you

1127
00:56:56,284 --> 00:57:00,500
♫ Melting the ice
throughout the night

1128
00:57:00,500 --> 00:57:02,589
[liquid pouring]

1129
00:57:02,589 --> 00:57:05,469
♫ Won't shed a tear

1130
00:57:05,469 --> 00:57:09,060
♫ And I'll keep holding on

1131
00:57:10,688 --> 00:57:14,320
♫ Until you come back to me

1132
00:57:16,115 --> 00:57:18,704
♫ Lonely night

1133
00:57:20,165 --> 00:57:22,461
♫ So lonely

1134
00:57:24,841 --> 00:57:28,348
♫ In such a distant world

1135
00:57:29,935 --> 00:57:33,024
♫ There is no choice

1136
00:57:34,443 --> 00:57:37,449
♫ I won't be afraid

1137
00:57:38,744 --> 00:57:42,919
♫ Now is the time to stand
strong against fate

1138
00:57:44,881 --> 00:57:48,054
♫ Feel me close

1139
00:57:48,054 --> 00:57:51,018
♫ Even when in pain

1140
00:57:52,020 --> 00:57:55,360
♫ Every day, everywhere

1141
00:57:58,868 --> 00:58:02,542
♫ I will love you eternally

1142
00:58:05,590 --> 00:58:09,471
♫ The stream of time

1143
00:58:09,471 --> 00:58:11,518
♫ Never stops

1144
00:58:11,518 --> 00:58:14,608
♫ Never sets me free

1145
00:58:15,943 --> 00:58:19,618
[gentle instrumental music]

1146
00:58:22,456 --> 00:58:25,212
[neon crackling]

1147
00:58:42,830 --> 00:58:45,753
[insects chirping]

1148
00:59:00,156 --> 00:59:03,622
‐ Oh, sorry, I must have nodded
off a second there.

1149
00:59:03,622 --> 00:59:05,543
‐ That's quite alright.

1150
00:59:07,087 --> 00:59:10,720
I'm glad that Mr. Teabolo is
getting some rest.

1151
00:59:10,720 --> 00:59:14,101
[dogs barking]

1152
00:59:14,101 --> 00:59:15,604
I'll go check it out.

1153
00:59:15,604 --> 00:59:18,192
[dogs barking]

1154
00:59:22,200 --> 00:59:23,036
[gasping]

1155
00:59:23,036 --> 00:59:25,708
Oh no, there's a fire
in the village.

1156
00:59:25,708 --> 00:59:28,296
[dogs barking]

1157
00:59:30,885 --> 00:59:33,222
[murmuring]

1158
00:59:35,393 --> 00:59:38,149
‐ Hey, hold it right there.

1159
00:59:38,149 --> 00:59:40,905
Stay where you are,
or we'll shoot.

1160
00:59:40,905 --> 00:59:43,451
‐ [Villager] Help,
somebody help us.

1161
00:59:43,451 --> 00:59:45,413
Please, you've got to help us.

1162
00:59:45,413 --> 00:59:46,248
Thugs came from the Bay

1163
00:59:46,248 --> 00:59:47,752
and started attacking
the village.

1164
00:59:47,752 --> 00:59:50,800
‐ Mr. Aznable's house
is on fire too.

1165
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:53,054
‐ They said they're going to
kill everyone in the park.

1166
00:59:53,054 --> 00:59:56,143
They said it's because we're all
Zeon supporters here.

1167
00:59:56,143 --> 00:59:58,439
‐ They're planning on
coming here too.

1168
00:59:58,439 --> 01:00:00,611
[gasping]

1169
01:00:01,445 --> 01:00:04,368
[glass shattering]

1170
01:00:06,205 --> 01:00:08,627
[gun firing]

1171
01:00:11,424 --> 01:00:15,432
[laughing and screaming]

1172
01:00:15,432 --> 01:00:17,687
‐ [Thug] Yeah, burn it all.

1173
01:00:19,273 --> 01:00:20,108
[murmuring]

1174
01:00:20,108 --> 01:00:22,613
[guns firing]

1175
01:00:23,740 --> 01:00:24,993
[car engine running]

1176
01:00:24,993 --> 01:00:27,080
‐ [Villager] Oh no,
they're here.

1177
01:00:27,080 --> 01:00:29,586
[guns firing]

1178
01:00:31,923 --> 01:00:35,890
[foreboding instrumental music]

1179
01:00:43,196 --> 01:00:45,951
‐ We're going to have to
build some barricades.

1180
01:00:45,951 --> 01:00:47,538
Seal up the doors and windows,

1181
01:00:47,538 --> 01:00:50,544
and prepare to fight
for your lives.

1182
01:00:55,386 --> 01:00:57,558
[glass shattering]

1183
01:00:57,558 --> 01:00:58,977
‐ What in the world?

1184
01:00:58,977 --> 01:00:59,812
Hey, wait.

1185
01:01:02,359 --> 01:01:03,862
Where's Sayla?

1186
01:01:03,862 --> 01:01:05,281
Where did she go?

1187
01:01:06,283 --> 01:01:07,118
Sayla.

1188
01:01:08,454 --> 01:01:10,458
‐ Sedatives, get the sedatives.

1189
01:01:10,458 --> 01:01:11,460
‐ Do we have weapons?

1190
01:01:11,460 --> 01:01:12,797
‐ Yes, we have plenty.

1191
01:01:12,797 --> 01:01:14,926
They're really old though.

1192
01:01:14,926 --> 01:01:16,136
How about this?

1193
01:01:16,136 --> 01:01:18,140
A Winchester model 1873,

1194
01:01:19,142 --> 01:01:20,688
it uses lever action.

1195
01:01:20,688 --> 01:01:22,274
It's loaded with eight bullets.

1196
01:01:22,274 --> 01:01:23,735
[guns firing]

1197
01:01:23,735 --> 01:01:26,323
[yelling and laughing]

1198
01:01:26,323 --> 01:01:28,745
[gun firing]

1199
01:01:42,272 --> 01:01:45,028
[gun cocking]

1200
01:01:45,028 --> 01:01:47,533
[guns firing]

1201
01:01:49,494 --> 01:01:50,914
‐ Those bastards.

1202
01:01:56,383 --> 01:01:59,056
[bomb exploding]

1203
01:02:02,145 --> 01:02:04,316
[yelling]

1204
01:02:05,653 --> 01:02:08,533
[gun firing]

1205
01:02:08,533 --> 01:02:10,871
[screaming]

1206
01:02:15,631 --> 01:02:17,425
‐ Bunch of animals,

1207
01:02:17,425 --> 01:02:19,221
Federation, Zeon,

1208
01:02:19,221 --> 01:02:21,141
they're all the same.

1209
01:02:21,141 --> 01:02:24,231
This is madness, pure madness.

1210
01:02:24,231 --> 01:02:26,151
[guns firing]

1211
01:02:26,151 --> 01:02:28,447
What drove them to this place,

1212
01:02:28,447 --> 01:02:30,368
hatred, greed?

1213
01:02:30,368 --> 01:02:32,873
[guns firing]

1214
01:02:34,084 --> 01:02:35,294
Or was it something else?

1215
01:02:35,294 --> 01:02:38,342
[car engine running]

1216
01:02:43,436 --> 01:02:46,275
[bombs exploding]

1217
01:02:48,404 --> 01:02:49,448
Don't run away.

1218
01:02:49,448 --> 01:02:51,368
Just put out that fire.

1219
01:02:54,667 --> 01:02:56,588
Head to the back of the
hall upstairs.

1220
01:02:56,588 --> 01:02:57,422
Don't worry.

1221
01:02:57,422 --> 01:02:58,842
You'll be fine.

1222
01:02:58,842 --> 01:02:59,844
‐ Excuse me.

1223
01:03:02,098 --> 01:03:05,939
[dramatic instrumental music]

1224
01:03:09,446 --> 01:03:11,534
[crying]

1225
01:03:13,496 --> 01:03:15,751
‐ I'm very sorry for your loss.

1226
01:03:15,751 --> 01:03:18,130
I tried to do
everything that I could,

1227
01:03:18,130 --> 01:03:21,846
but all this chaos was just
too much for him.

1228
01:03:21,846 --> 01:03:23,934
[crying]

1229
01:03:33,954 --> 01:03:37,628
[gentle instrumental music]

1230
01:03:44,600 --> 01:03:46,938
‐ Mr. Teabolo, I'm so sorry.

1231
01:03:48,608 --> 01:03:50,529
You did so much for us,

1232
01:03:56,373 --> 01:03:57,626
so thank you.

1233
01:03:57,626 --> 01:04:00,674
You were a wonderful father.

1234
01:04:00,674 --> 01:04:02,928
You really, truly were.

1235
01:04:02,928 --> 01:04:04,682
[crying]

1236
01:04:04,682 --> 01:04:08,355
[gentle instrumental music]

1237
01:04:21,674 --> 01:04:24,012
[murmuring]

1238
01:04:27,978 --> 01:04:30,734
[fire crackling]

1239
01:04:34,533 --> 01:04:35,786
‐ What is that?

1240
01:04:37,330 --> 01:04:38,457
Is it dawn already?

1241
01:04:38,457 --> 01:04:40,378
‐ [Thug] No, it can't be.

1242
01:04:40,378 --> 01:04:43,133
[station exploding]

1243
01:04:43,133 --> 01:04:45,931
‐ Miranda Bay, it's [screaming].

1244
01:04:45,931 --> 01:04:48,268
‐ It's under attack now too?

1245
01:04:52,653 --> 01:04:55,366
[bombs exploding]

1246
01:04:55,366 --> 01:04:56,201
[screaming]

1247
01:04:56,201 --> 01:04:57,830
‐ Please remain calm.

1248
01:04:57,830 --> 01:04:59,416
Everyone, take your seats

1249
01:04:59,416 --> 01:05:01,963
and fasten your seatbelts‐‐

1250
01:05:01,963 --> 01:05:05,846
‐ Oh, Roger, I really believed
we'd see our son again.

1251
01:05:05,846 --> 01:05:07,473
[murmuring]

1252
01:05:07,473 --> 01:05:10,479
[station exploding]

1253
01:05:16,324 --> 01:05:20,499
[foreboding instrumental music]

1254
01:05:20,499 --> 01:05:23,380
‐ Artesia, if there
is such a thing

1255
01:05:23,380 --> 01:05:25,886
as divine protection,

1256
01:05:25,886 --> 01:05:30,061
then I have faith that you are
not here right now.

1257
01:05:34,653 --> 01:05:35,655
Texas, what?

1258
01:05:39,872 --> 01:05:41,751
‐ The Bay has been destroyed.

1259
01:05:41,751 --> 01:05:44,130
We can't go back now.

1260
01:05:44,130 --> 01:05:46,301
[yelling]

1261
01:05:54,568 --> 01:05:58,367
[dramatic instrumental music]

1262
01:06:10,099 --> 01:06:12,478
‐ [Tachi] The pilot of a
red Mobile Suit,

1263
01:06:12,478 --> 01:06:14,315
the pilot of a red Mobile Suit.

1264
01:06:14,315 --> 01:06:17,071
‐ The pilot of a red
Mobile Suit.

1265
01:06:22,916 --> 01:06:25,087
[yelling]

1266
01:06:27,801 --> 01:06:31,224
[rocket engines running]

1267
01:06:43,498 --> 01:06:47,507
[foreboding instrumental music]

1268
01:06:52,266 --> 01:06:54,855
‐ So Miranda's been attacked,
huh?

1269
01:06:54,855 --> 01:06:56,525
‐ Yes, there are multiple
damage reports

1270
01:06:56,525 --> 01:06:58,487
from all Side Five Banshees,

1271
01:06:58,487 --> 01:06:59,531
and those reports indicate

1272
01:06:59,531 --> 01:07:00,659
that their docking bay sections

1273
01:07:00,659 --> 01:07:02,788
have been largely crippled.

1274
01:07:02,788 --> 01:07:04,415
‐ This doesn't make sense.

1275
01:07:04,415 --> 01:07:05,585
I would have thought
Zeon would want

1276
01:07:05,585 --> 01:07:08,006
to focus all its efforts on
a fleet battle.

1277
01:07:08,006 --> 01:07:09,342
‐ Perhaps we should
divert some ships

1278
01:07:09,342 --> 01:07:10,679
to defend Loum.

1279
01:07:10,679 --> 01:07:12,223
‐ COO, analysis.

1280
01:07:12,223 --> 01:07:14,018
‐ If any of the fleets
were to go to Loum,

1281
01:07:14,018 --> 01:07:16,189
based on coordinates, we
the second fleet

1282
01:07:16,189 --> 01:07:17,400
would be the closest.

1283
01:07:17,400 --> 01:07:18,736
However, we are also the ones

1284
01:07:18,736 --> 01:07:22,243
who are located closest to
the Zeon fleet.

1285
01:07:23,746 --> 01:07:24,873
‐ If we turned around now,

1286
01:07:24,873 --> 01:07:27,879
we'd be attacked from behind
by Dozle's ships.

1287
01:07:27,879 --> 01:07:30,342
We'll have to leave Loum
to Reval then.

1288
01:07:30,342 --> 01:07:32,639
After all, we only
initiated this operation

1289
01:07:32,639 --> 01:07:36,062
based on intelligence that
Reval himself received.

1290
01:07:36,062 --> 01:07:40,070
[foreboding instrumental music]

1291
01:07:47,043 --> 01:07:49,923
‐ The enemy has hit
Miranda's Bay.

1292
01:07:49,923 --> 01:07:51,009
‐ Yes, and not only that,

1293
01:07:51,009 --> 01:07:52,596
the garrison fleet is
stuck there,

1294
01:07:52,596 --> 01:07:55,059
so they are requesting for
our assistance.

1295
01:07:55,059 --> 01:07:55,935
‐ I see.

1296
01:07:55,935 --> 01:07:57,981
We did not anticipate this.

1297
01:07:57,981 --> 01:07:59,317
‐ The area's docking
bay sections

1298
01:07:59,317 --> 01:08:01,237
have been heavily damaged.

1299
01:08:01,237 --> 01:08:02,406
‐ The Loum government
has issued‐‐

1300
01:08:02,406 --> 01:08:04,745
‐ They're even covering the
incident on the news.

1301
01:08:04,745 --> 01:08:06,456
‐ Shall we divert some of
the Tianum fleet

1302
01:08:06,456 --> 01:08:07,793
to assist them?

1303
01:08:07,793 --> 01:08:09,505
‐ That's not a good option.

1304
01:08:09,505 --> 01:08:10,590
Tianum's got his hands full

1305
01:08:10,590 --> 01:08:13,679
facing off against almost the
entire Zeon fleet.

1306
01:08:13,679 --> 01:08:16,685
I doubt he wants to
divert a single ship.

1307
01:08:16,685 --> 01:08:19,733
With that said, we must act.

1308
01:08:19,733 --> 01:08:22,196
Send Cunningham and Walking's
fleets over there.

1309
01:08:22,196 --> 01:08:23,031
‐ Yes, sir.

1310
01:08:23,031 --> 01:08:24,660
‐ Also, dispatch supply
and landing ships

1311
01:08:24,660 --> 01:08:27,164
to provide aid to the
civilians in that area.

1312
01:08:27,164 --> 01:08:28,125
‐ Yes.

1313
01:08:28,125 --> 01:08:29,502
‐ Inform the bridge
that the combined

1314
01:08:29,502 --> 01:08:32,174
first and third fleet will stay
on its current course.

1315
01:08:32,174 --> 01:08:33,135
‐ [Officer] Yes, sir.

1316
01:08:33,135 --> 01:08:35,890
‐ Alright, men, looks like we're
upping our timeline.

1317
01:08:35,890 --> 01:08:37,727
‐ [Officers] Yes, sir.

1318
01:08:40,065 --> 01:08:42,403
[foreboding instrumental music]

1319
01:08:42,403 --> 01:08:44,323
‐ Uh, begging your pardon, sir.

1320
01:08:44,323 --> 01:08:46,453
Our fleet has arrived at the
final defense line

