01:08:46,453 --> 01:08:50,210
in the orbit between Side
Three and the Moon.

1322
01:08:52,716 --> 01:08:55,012
Ever since Vice Admiral
Dozle's fleet,

1323
01:08:55,012 --> 01:08:57,809
which is at the core of this
operation, set sail,

1324
01:08:57,809 --> 01:08:59,855
he has been advancing
towards the Loum front

1325
01:08:59,855 --> 01:09:01,525
under radio silence.

1326
01:09:02,694 --> 01:09:06,869
‐ To our fatherland, to the
principality of Zeon, salute.

1327
01:09:10,083 --> 01:09:12,547
‐ [Officer] As you can see, the
fleet has already spread out

1328
01:09:12,547 --> 01:09:14,843
and taken battle formation‐‐

1329
01:09:14,843 --> 01:09:16,346
‐ How frustrating.

1330
01:09:16,346 --> 01:09:18,851
Hey, father, I mean sovereign,

1331
01:09:19,811 --> 01:09:21,690
I think I made the
wrong decision.

1332
01:09:21,690 --> 01:09:23,903
I should have requested a
position in the space forces,

1333
01:09:23,903 --> 01:09:25,030
not the ground forces.

1334
01:09:25,030 --> 01:09:25,865
‐ No, strike that.

1335
01:09:25,865 --> 01:09:28,161
I have a new report on the
enemy's activity.

1336
01:09:28,161 --> 01:09:30,667
The rebel fleet has split
into two groups.

1337
01:09:30,667 --> 01:09:32,879
One has changed course
towards Loum.

1338
01:09:32,879 --> 01:09:33,881
They appear to have fallen

1339
01:09:33,881 --> 01:09:35,802
for our diversionary operation.

1340
01:09:35,802 --> 01:09:38,849
This alters our relative
fighting strengths considerably.

1341
01:09:38,849 --> 01:09:41,271
It is now roughly three to one.

1342
01:09:41,271 --> 01:09:42,774
We have also just
received a report

1343
01:09:42,774 --> 01:09:45,530
from the commando team that
was sent to Loum.

1344
01:09:45,530 --> 01:09:47,074
‐ That's the team
that Char's in.

1345
01:09:47,074 --> 01:09:48,995
‐ [Officer] Attack successful,

1346
01:09:48,995 --> 01:09:50,080
mission accomplished,

1347
01:09:50,080 --> 01:09:52,459
no losses to friendly forces.

1348
01:09:52,459 --> 01:09:54,590
Upon retrieval of
Mobile Suit forces,

1349
01:09:54,590 --> 01:09:55,925
you will make for the Loum area

1350
01:09:55,925 --> 01:09:58,388
and rendezvous with Special
Assault Regiment.

1351
01:09:58,388 --> 01:10:02,396
[foreboding instrumental music]

1352
01:10:06,864 --> 01:10:10,162
‐ Alright, men, this is the
battle we've been waiting for.

1353
01:10:10,162 --> 01:10:12,959
The curtain's rising on a
new kind of warfare,

1354
01:10:12,959 --> 01:10:16,049
and you will be the lead actors
in the opening act.

1355
01:10:16,049 --> 01:10:17,886
We have one goal here,

1356
01:10:17,886 --> 01:10:21,059
and that is to beat
the Federation.

1357
01:10:21,059 --> 01:10:24,148
If we win, the
world's our oyster.

1358
01:10:24,148 --> 01:10:27,237
Rank, glory, and bonuses,
all around.

1359
01:10:28,658 --> 01:10:30,828
‐ Plus there's one more thing.

1360
01:10:30,828 --> 01:10:32,456
There's a punk out
there named Char

1361
01:10:32,456 --> 01:10:34,085
with a red suit.

1362
01:10:34,085 --> 01:10:37,174
You better make sure we
outperform that guy.

1363
01:10:37,174 --> 01:10:39,470
There's no way he's
getting the prize,

1364
01:10:39,470 --> 01:10:41,307
not out from under us.

1365
01:10:41,307 --> 01:10:42,769
Let's do this.

1366
01:10:42,769 --> 01:10:45,023
[cheering]

1367
01:10:45,023 --> 01:10:46,610
[dramatic instrumental music]

1368
01:10:46,610 --> 01:10:50,033
[rocket engines running]

1369
01:11:03,018 --> 01:11:05,397
‐ [Officer] The Tianum fleet is
almost within firing range

1370
01:11:05,397 --> 01:11:06,482
of the enemy.

1371
01:11:07,819 --> 01:11:10,742
‐ Alright, go ahead and give
them the permission to engage,

1372
01:11:10,742 --> 01:11:12,411
and the Minovsky
Particle status?

1373
01:11:12,411 --> 01:11:15,417
[electronic beeping]

1374
01:11:15,417 --> 01:11:17,672
‐ Not good, it's already
causing some interference

1375
01:11:17,672 --> 01:11:20,636
with our radar and data links.

1376
01:11:20,636 --> 01:11:22,014
‐ Recon craft status.

1377
01:11:22,014 --> 01:11:23,058
‐ Handled, sir.

1378
01:11:23,058 --> 01:11:24,603
We've put together an
extra rotation

1379
01:11:24,603 --> 01:11:26,439
in addition to our
regular patrols.

1380
01:11:26,439 --> 01:11:29,195
[rocket engines running]

1381
01:11:29,195 --> 01:11:30,072
We've had them circling

1382
01:11:30,072 --> 01:11:33,244
the region nonstop
since this morning.

1383
01:11:34,288 --> 01:11:37,044
‐ Warfare has no choice
but to change.

1384
01:11:37,044 --> 01:11:39,048
Let's head up to the bridge.

1385
01:11:39,048 --> 01:11:41,804
Update me with new intel
as it comes in.

1386
01:11:41,804 --> 01:11:43,098
‐ Yes, sir.

1387
01:11:43,098 --> 01:11:45,393
‐ Distance now less than 10,000.

1388
01:11:45,393 --> 01:11:48,943
Enemy composition, three
battleship groups‐‐

1389
01:11:48,943 --> 01:11:51,489
‐ Dammit, this is aggravating.

1390
01:11:51,489 --> 01:11:54,370
I'm just stuck here
watching all this.

1391
01:11:54,370 --> 01:11:56,457
I bet you Char's in
the thick of it.

1392
01:11:56,457 --> 01:11:58,629
He's probably pursuing the
enemy fleet right now.

1393
01:11:58,629 --> 01:12:00,550
‐ That's enough, Garma.

1394
01:12:01,927 --> 01:12:05,350
In this world, there are those
whose deaths do not matter.

1395
01:12:05,350 --> 01:12:08,064
Then there are those to whom
it is not permitted.

1396
01:12:08,064 --> 01:12:10,193
You must prepare
yourself to be ready

1397
01:12:10,193 --> 01:12:11,780
when the time comes.

1398
01:12:11,780 --> 01:12:13,909
‐ With all due respect father,

1399
01:12:13,909 --> 01:12:16,497
I cannot be systematic when it
comes to people's lives

1400
01:12:16,497 --> 01:12:17,542
at a time like this.

1401
01:12:17,542 --> 01:12:18,878
‐ [Officer] Minovsky
Particle dispersal

1402
01:12:18,878 --> 01:12:20,756
appears to be increasing.

1403
01:12:20,756 --> 01:12:23,136
Density increase is sustaining.

1404
01:12:23,136 --> 01:12:25,850
Visual feed quality
is degrading.

1405
01:12:25,850 --> 01:12:28,104
The battle is about to begin.

1406
01:12:28,104 --> 01:12:32,446
[dramatic instrumental music]

1407
01:12:32,446 --> 01:12:33,657
‐ [Man] Minovsky
Particle density

1408
01:12:33,657 --> 01:12:34,743
has reached a combat level.

1409
01:12:34,743 --> 01:12:35,912
‐ [Man] Capacitor is
holding steady.

1410
01:12:35,912 --> 01:12:37,582
‐ [Man] Bearing 181 confirmed.

1411
01:12:37,582 --> 01:12:40,838
‐ All hands prepare to
initiate barrage.

1412
01:12:40,838 --> 01:12:42,216
‐ All hands ready the canons.

1413
01:12:42,216 --> 01:12:43,552
‐ All hands ready the canons.

1414
01:12:43,552 --> 01:12:44,638
‐ Prepare to fire.

1415
01:12:44,638 --> 01:12:46,265
‐ Loading of launch tubes one,
two, three confirmed.

1416
01:12:46,265 --> 01:12:47,977
‐ Switching system over
to canon fire.

1417
01:12:47,977 --> 01:12:49,355
‐ [Man] Stabilizers activated.

1418
01:12:49,355 --> 01:12:50,608
Safety is disengaged.

1419
01:12:50,608 --> 01:12:53,404
‐ [Man] Bearing 181, 012.

1420
01:12:53,404 --> 01:12:54,699
‐ [Man] Parameters entered.

1421
01:12:54,699 --> 01:12:56,118
‐ Here we go.

1422
01:12:56,118 --> 01:12:58,164
Commence barrage.

1423
01:12:58,164 --> 01:13:00,920
[weapons firing]

1424
01:13:06,932 --> 01:13:09,436
‐ [Officer] Our fleet has
launched a first attack.

1425
01:13:09,436 --> 01:13:11,984
‐ But the enemy has
better firing range.

1426
01:13:11,984 --> 01:13:13,027
‐ That is correct,

1427
01:13:13,027 --> 01:13:15,156
but it is not a concern of ours.

1428
01:13:15,156 --> 01:13:16,785
While our firepower is inferior

1429
01:13:16,785 --> 01:13:18,079
to the Federation's,

1430
01:13:18,079 --> 01:13:21,085
our fleet's Musai class has
excellent hit deflection

1431
01:13:21,085 --> 01:13:23,089
due to its smaller
cross section,

1432
01:13:23,089 --> 01:13:24,676
and the maneuverability
from the placement

1433
01:13:24,676 --> 01:13:26,262
of its thruster nozzles

1434
01:13:26,262 --> 01:13:27,932
allows it to easily
take evasive‐‐

1435
01:13:27,932 --> 01:13:29,978
[yelling]

1436
01:13:29,978 --> 01:13:31,523
‐ What was‐‐

1437
01:13:31,523 --> 01:13:33,819
‐ One of our ships was hit.

1438
01:13:33,819 --> 01:13:35,071
Looks like it was a direct hit.

1439
01:13:35,071 --> 01:13:36,575
‐ Whose ship?

1440
01:13:36,575 --> 01:13:38,494
It wasn't Dozle's Valkyrie,
was it?

1441
01:13:38,494 --> 01:13:40,081
‐ [Officer] Uh, no, sir.

1442
01:13:40,081 --> 01:13:42,461
‐ But a hit is still a hit,

1443
01:13:42,461 --> 01:13:46,052
and what was that about
maneuverability, huh?

1444
01:13:46,052 --> 01:13:48,306
You said it had great
hit deflection.

1445
01:13:48,306 --> 01:13:49,642
The battle's only just begun,

1446
01:13:49,642 --> 01:13:51,688
and one of our ships has been
destroyed already‐‐

1447
01:13:51,688 --> 01:13:52,523
‐ Garman.

1448
01:13:54,360 --> 01:13:56,030
You are embarrassing yourself.

1449
01:13:56,030 --> 01:13:57,784
Calm down right now.

1450
01:13:57,784 --> 01:14:00,497
[weapons firing]

1451
01:14:13,272 --> 01:14:15,611
[screaming]

1452
01:14:20,161 --> 01:14:22,416
‐ [Man] [murmuring]
Heavily damaged‐‐

1453
01:14:22,416 --> 01:14:24,044
‐ [Man] That's the third ship of
our advanced fleet

1454
01:14:24,044 --> 01:14:25,046
that we've lost.

1455
01:14:25,046 --> 01:14:26,340
‐ [Man] Seltovic,
engines offline.

1456
01:14:26,340 --> 01:14:28,971
‐ [Man] Proton and Amagie both
appear to have been hit.

1457
01:14:28,971 --> 01:14:31,225
‐ [Man] [murmuring] Has given
the order to abandon ship.

1458
01:14:31,225 --> 01:14:34,983
‐ Okay, we're going to be
altering our formation.

1459
01:14:34,983 --> 01:14:36,903
Inform the rest of the fleet.

1460
01:14:36,903 --> 01:14:38,448
Do not panic.

1461
01:14:38,448 --> 01:14:41,036
Disperse and change heading
while returning fire.

1462
01:14:41,036 --> 01:14:43,291
From here on out,
it's do or die.

1463
01:14:43,291 --> 01:14:45,086
Now get on with it.

1464
01:14:45,086 --> 01:14:46,548
[weapons firing]

1465
01:14:46,548 --> 01:14:50,388
[dramatic instrumental music]

1466
01:15:03,832 --> 01:15:05,168
‐ It looks like
they'll be wiped out

1467
01:15:05,168 --> 01:15:07,297
in our first engagement,

1468
01:15:07,297 --> 01:15:08,967
those Zeon bastards.

1469
01:15:09,761 --> 01:15:12,517
[weapons firing]

1470
01:15:13,392 --> 01:15:17,234
[dramatic instrumental music]

1471
01:15:37,232 --> 01:15:39,111
‐ Excuse me, the Tianum
fleet has begun

1472
01:15:39,111 --> 01:15:41,198
to engage the enemy, sir.

1473
01:15:47,502 --> 01:15:49,172
[laughing]

1474
01:15:49,172 --> 01:15:52,972
[dramatic instrumental music]

1475
01:16:03,952 --> 01:16:04,912
‐ [Char] I'm launching.

1476
01:16:04,912 --> 01:16:06,498
Open the hatch.

1477
01:16:06,498 --> 01:16:07,627
‐ [Dren] I think it's
best you wait

1478
01:16:07,627 --> 01:16:10,381
until the captain gives the
order, Lieutenant Char.

1479
01:16:10,381 --> 01:16:12,010
‐ I'll remind you that I'm
the one in charge

1480
01:16:12,010 --> 01:16:14,682
of the attack team, Ensign Dren.

1481
01:16:16,268 --> 01:16:17,688
I'm going in ahead.

1482
01:16:17,688 --> 01:16:20,485
Dena, take command of the
team and follow me.

1483
01:16:20,485 --> 01:16:21,403
Can you do that?

1484
01:16:21,403 --> 01:16:22,782
‐ [Dena] On it, sir.

1485
01:16:22,782 --> 01:16:25,036
‐ Man, oh man, looks like
being teamed up

1486
01:16:25,036 --> 01:16:26,706
with the winner of
the Zeon Cross

1487
01:16:26,706 --> 01:16:28,669
is gonna be bad for our health,
sir.

1488
01:16:28,669 --> 01:16:30,213
‐ Initiate launch.

1489
01:16:30,213 --> 01:16:32,008
‐ Okay, bosun, can you confirm

1490
01:16:32,008 --> 01:16:33,762
that he has clearance?

1491
01:16:33,762 --> 01:16:36,058
‐ Launch procedures are a go.

1492
01:16:36,058 --> 01:16:39,899
[dramatic instrumental music]

1493
01:16:50,713 --> 01:16:54,052
[rocket engines firing]

1494
01:17:01,568 --> 01:17:05,408
‐ [Dren] All units, proceed to
combat area at full speed.

1495
01:17:05,408 --> 01:17:06,870
‐ Just like we practiced.

1496
01:17:06,870 --> 01:17:08,164
‐ And don't fall behind.

1497
01:17:08,164 --> 01:17:10,669
‐ You're gonna form up on me.

1498
01:17:10,669 --> 01:17:14,092
[rocket engines running]

1499
01:17:14,092 --> 01:17:16,221
[dramatic instrumental music]

1500
01:17:16,221 --> 01:17:18,977
[weapons firing]

1501
01:17:36,470 --> 01:17:40,311
[dramatic instrumental music]

1502
01:17:49,997 --> 01:17:53,087
[electronic beeping]

1503
01:17:54,130 --> 01:17:56,761
[alarm beeping]

1504
01:18:01,228 --> 01:18:03,482
[grunting]

1505
01:18:20,559 --> 01:18:23,648
[electronic beeping]

1506
01:18:24,692 --> 01:18:25,652
‐ There it is.

1507
01:18:25,652 --> 01:18:27,363
I found their main force.

1508
01:18:27,363 --> 01:18:31,204
[dramatic instrumental music]

1509
01:18:40,014 --> 01:18:42,937
I'm changing the
course of history.

1510
01:18:45,859 --> 01:18:48,531
[alarm beeping]

1511
01:18:50,702 --> 01:18:54,794
Be amazed at what I am capable
of, oh mighty one.

1512
01:19:05,231 --> 01:19:08,905
[gentle instrumental music]

1513
01:19:31,743 --> 01:19:35,751
[singing in a foreign language]

